{"product_id": "39160", "page": 3, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-11-27", "text": "Remember that feeling you had when playing Dungeon Siege II with your friends and everyone was having a blast I mean there was so much to do!! The hidden levels, the tough enemies... Well this game is nothing like that... I restarted the game 3 times with a different character and still managed to finish the base game in under 12 hours... And it wan't fun doing it either. I kept hoping maybe I'm missing something it'll get better. Then the end game credits pop up and you realize you could have spent your time better by skydiving without a parachute for example...", "hours": 12.7, "user_id": "76561198043584714", "username": "Splitcore", "products": 34, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 3, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-11-27", "text": "If you loved the original Dungeon Siege and Dungeon Siege 2, completely forget anything and everything you knew or cared for from them if you begin this game. Like to customize characters to any degree? Not here. Like an actual party of adventurers to control, balancing between melee and magic, archery and armor? Not here.", "hours": 5.7, "user_id": "76561198138258670", "username": "Atreyu_92", "products": 69, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
