{"product_id": "39160", "page": 5, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-09-30", "text": "Compared with the previous titles in the Dungeon Siege games, this is a clear downhill slide. The playable characters are very narrow in terms of development both story-wise and skill-wise. Controlling a sizeable but managable team is missing too. You are narrowed down to your main character and one of the discarded classes that you didn't chose in the beginning. While you can exchange your companion, the idea leading a group of heroes is lost. Controls are okay-ish while the camera behaves quit annoying at times.", "hours": 5.1, "username": "Rumo", "products": 64, "early_access": false}
