{"product_id": "39160", "page": 7, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-28", "text": "Maybe not the best of its genre, but definitely worth picking up on sale if you're a fan of hack n slash RPG's. Especially if you want to couch co-op with a friend. Check out the\nI made with my friend and see our first impressions.", "hours": 41.0, "username": "Hardshot Dave", "products": 343, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 7, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-27", "text": "One of the best couch co op games I have ever played. Dungeon Siege III offers a captivating story that can be influenced by the player during some key conversations with other characters - do you kill your first opponent or set her free? Do you chose to be open about your character's heritage or keep it a secret? Do you remove the sacred artifact from its resting place in the tomb or let it rest in piece?\nThe game offers 4 playable characters with unique abilities. Abilities, armor, weapons and trait-boosting artifacts can be upgraded regularly.\nThe world of Ehb is so detailed, beautiful and many-faceted, I can barely describe it. Especially including the DLC, your really feel emerged in this world.\nI bought the whole Dungeon Siege collection for 4\u20ac during the last summer sale. This third part alone would have been worth way more.", "hours": 57.6, "user_id": "76561197971965535", "username": "burnsky", "products": 515, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 7, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-19", "text": "Not what I was expecting after DS II, but decent in its own right. I find it enjoyable.\nLess customizations, less party people, less hidden things to find. Have to go more out of your way to gain XP outside of the storyline.", "hours": 61.9, "user_id": "76561197978594500", "username": "Evil_Piggies", "products": 124, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 7, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-16", "text": "Play this game if you're looking to disrupt the basic Diablo 2/3 /Torchlight point and click game. (those are awesome; break from them for this) I went from D3 straight to this and struggled mightly. Once I reset myself I found a rewarding game that balanced area effect, offense, and defense how I wanted to play.\nTry the different characters and play this game. Its not diablo and its not trying to be. Enjoy both.", "hours": 25.0, "user_id": "76561197972366861", "username": "dearinma", "products": 55, "early_access": false}
