{"product_id": "39160", "page": 8, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-24", "text": "The graphics are amazing; everything else is boring.\nThe artistic direction is truly wonderful; I especially enjoy Anjali's design. Unfortunately, the rest of the game is terribly tedious:\n-killing baddies feels unsatisfying, which is a shame for an ARPG.\n-the loot system should not even exist since its main draw -to customize your character according to the items you choose- is not in the game. You can safely play through the whole game without looking at the item's stats, instead just picking whichever ones have the highest gold value.\n-the story is entirely uninteresting. No twists, no emotion.\nI played through the whole game on the highest difficulty, but on the last level I just skipped all the mobs and went straight for the final boss. I've never done that before.\nDisappointing.", "hours": 17.9, "username": "Demicore", "products": 165, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
