{"product_id": "39160", "page": 9, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-10", "text": "Very nice story, about 17 hours of gameplay for me on one playthrough completing all quests. Certainly worth the play, don't let the negative reviews fool you. I used an Xbox 360 controller instead of M&K and I think it made a really large difference in gameplay. Certainly begs for multiple plays with different main characters, whether to take all the achievements home or just to experience the story in multiple versions, it's a delight to play.", "hours": 17.9, "user_id": "76561198068150202", "username": "Father Heretic", "products": 22, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 9, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-05-30", "text": "Ughhh... Seeing all the positive reviews makes me sad, but I can understand them if people hadn't played the  first two. Dungeon Siege III is well... Not  a Dungeon Siege game... it's more like an over the shoulder hack and slash, there are no parties, no character specs, and as far as I know, no real story that follows anything like the first two. I have tried to play this game on multipule occasions but I cannot bring myself to enjoy it. I don't recommend for fans of the series, but I do recommend it if you have never played the first two.", "hours": 1.1, "username": "Reggit", "products": 230, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 9, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-05-29", "text": "This game actually isn't too bad. Looks good, plays well and it's challenging.\nHowever, i can completely understand a lot of the negativity. This game isn't anything like the previous titles in the series. And personally i also would have much preferred a real DS title. But if i'm objective, i can recommend this as a decent fun enough hack & slash title. Especially if you can get it during a sale. Gas Powered games is pretty much gone, so i don't think we'll ever have a real successor.", "hours": 18.6, "username": "Dj El Marriachi", "products": 103, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 9, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-05-25", "text": "A decent enough game in itself.  However fans of the series prepare to be disappointed.  It shares very little in common with the Dungeon Siege I that we love and the Dungeon Siege II that was a pretty good followup.  They did away with the groups and instead made it a single character focused game.  Fairly disappointed in it and I hope that one day they will find their roots again.", "hours": 35.6, "user_id": "76561198026899259", "username": "Duxbellorum", "products": 36, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 9, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-05-22", "text": "This is not like Dungeon Siege I and II, but its a Ok game, you will have some hours of fun.", "hours": 8.2, "username": "Pai do Mato  ( \u0361\u00b0 \u035c\u0296 \u0361\u00b0)", "products": 187, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 10, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-05-21", "text": "Eh. The graphics are good but the gameplay isn't. You can tell right away how the combat is going to be, and it's not fluid at all.", "hours": 0.4, "compensation": "Product received for free", "username": "Dan is Online", "products": 157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 10, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-04-26", "text": "While nothing like its two previous entrys, this game does have some charm. I recommend playing this game with a gamepad as it feels smoother. Difficulty spikes are here and there, even on casual, as some of the enemies hit hard and fast. Storyline is kind of blagh but it gets the point across. I recommend for anyone who enjoys a good action RPG and has nothing else to play. Pick it up on sale!", "hours": 15.3, "username": "Expendable", "products": 735, "early_access": false}
