{"product_id": "39160", "page": 14, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-19", "text": "I was very unhappy with this game in comparison to Dungeon Siege 2.  However, comparing this game to others of the same type and genre out there, it is actually good.  It would be better if it had a different name.  As a follow up to Dungeon Siege 2, it sucks.  As a stand alone game compared to others out there, it is not too bad....6.5 outta 10", "hours": 43.5, "user_id": "76561198112597048", "username": "lmz", "products": 35, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 14, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-16", "text": "Loved this game. The story was entertaining and some elements reminded me of a Salman Rushdie novel. Just fantastic. I read a guide before playing to choose the most OP toon and get the right abilities without having to spend ages thinking about it. As a result i picked the Gipsy and this helped me enjoy the story a lot and own all the enemies no problem. Environments are nice, it's cartoony but its well done. Clocked it in 40-50 hours which is great, didn't bother to replay with other toons or try multiplayer. If you get it at a discount, which happens a lot, you won't go wrong.", "hours": 56.5, "user_id": "76561198078131261", "username": "Awesome'sauce", "products": 91, "early_access": false}
