{"product_id": "39160", "page": 15, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-03", "text": "I had more fun with Dungeon Siege III than I expected. It isn't amazing, but a solid good experience.", "hours": 24.8, "username": "Mantrid", "products": 123, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 15, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-30", "text": "If you are buying this only because you liked the previous titles, DON'T. It's nothing like the previous games and that's not necesssarily a bad thing. I personally found this game extremely fun, with great replay value and I previously owned it on my Xbox360 so I've spent +100hours of whatever my steam account says.\nPros\n>Storyline seems linear, but if you read into it you'll find otherwise\n>Combat is fun and challenging\n>All characters play differently and thanks to the ToTS DLC you can do all sorts of different builds\n>Playing on hardcore could lead to you dying a lot to certain bosses, but you get iframes on your dodge and by studying   the boss you can flawless them. Kinda like Dark Souls\n>Your companions actually have a personality which is certainly a change from other games\n>Deeds are hidden until achieved, so you get what you deserve\n>All abilities are incredibly satisfying to use\n>Your choices actually change the ending\n>Katarina\nCons\n>Jeyne Kassynder\n>Odo\n>Camera can be a bit iffy, but I personally used my mouse to move around so I never had a problem with it\n>Jeyne Kassynder\n>The enchanting system can be really rage inducing. I disenchanted my +96 Doom spear and got nothing. (Good thing I had a better one)\n>Jeyne Kassynder\n^We get it Odo, you hate her\nOverall the game is extremely fun and has great replay value, but it is very different than the previos titles, which I also loved\nPS: I would literally marry the Dapper Old Gent if I could\nPSS: If you have Lucas as a follower, don't let him get too excited. He has this weird glitch where instead of traveling 15 meters with his dash, he shoots of into the nearest wall, which may be kilometers away. Fun to watch though", "hours": 45.8, "user_id": "76561198080177605", "username": "Aquatic Negro", "products": 50, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 15, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-12-28", "text": "This game is a huge let down, as I was very excited to start playing it after completing the previous two dungeon siege games.\nInstead of it being a true open world game where you are free to  explore vast areas, you have to go down narrow passageways to get to anywhere on the map.\nThe storyline is boring and the cutscenes are dreadful.\nIf you play as Lucus you will probably give up as he is impossible to play as; you have to go right next to the person you are attacking.\nHowever, for me there are two major things that disappointed me about this game; the lack of customisation of your character and the horrifically annoying camera angle.\nSo no, I do not recommend this game, it is one of the worst games I have ever played.", "hours": 9.7, "username": "dap2002", "products": 76, "early_access": false}
