{"product_id": "39160", "page": 25, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-08", "text": "It's a fun little action RPG. Not quite as many options as the originals in terms of choice and flexibility, and there is limited opacity in what each of the stats mean without digging into the manual, but hey. It's trying something new and it kinda worked. Not entirely, as it shifts from what I knew and loved about Dungeon Siege and replaces it with more hack-and-slashy gameplay, but it works. And for whatever reason, I miss the rather free-form nature of the older games.", "hours": 18.3, "user_id": "76561198017328264", "username": "queekoneeye", "products": 329, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 25, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-06", "text": "\"Dungeon of Fable 3 - Diablo\" is anything but a Dungeon Siege game, you get loot with every kill and there are so many treasure chests it makes you wonder the meaning of the word treasure. The combat is a farcry from the originals and you can only play as pre-made characters all of which are humans. Truly a step backwards in the franchise, but what can you expect after such a long time between sequels.\nSo why am I giving this a positive review ? Simple, it's a good game, just not what you'ld expect of a true Dungeon Siege title.", "hours": 8.2, "user_id": "76561198067430234", "username": "Alternative Trash Bin", "products": 180, "early_access": false}
