{"product_id": "39160", "page": 26, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-03", "text": "If you look at the other reviews, a lot of them are extreme fans of the previous 2 installments and cannot cope with the game changes in this one. Dungeon Siege 3 is actually a pretty decent game, it's kinda like RPG-lite but with a bit more background lore to it. Anyway, I'm having fun with the game and I think I could easily see it through to the end :)", "hours": 7.5, "user_id": "76561198052635370", "username": "Didymus", "products": 489, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 26, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-02", "text": "Much better than expected based on the other reviews I've read. Interesting story and fun gameplay. Just don't expect it to be an enhancement of the first two Dungeon Siege games, as this one is much different. It feels more like the Baldur's Gate and Champions of Norrath games which were released on consoles.", "hours": 31.6, "user_id": "76561197992609031", "username": "Funkybob", "products": 269, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 26, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-02-28", "text": "The gameplay is pretty weird! Was expecting more in that point though... Same with the story, it was really confusing and bad in my opinion so it's a big no for me.", "hours": 4.2, "user_id": "76561197986223876", "username": "Mr. Frippe", "products": 162, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 26, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-26", "text": "I wasn't too sure about this game from the start as I like when games stay true to their base. As I started playing I was astounded by the graphics and solid gameplay throughout. The Framerate stays solid with no lag or tearing. Even Mid to low range machines can play this game flawlessly with no issue. With it's Steampunk/Anime staging and deeply engaging storyline it is sure to keep you interested all through your journey. With a balanced ablility tree with defensive offensive and passive powers there is no battle you cannot win.  The Armor system alone in this game is unique as you have to really think about how to balance your gear for maximum effect.  Agility is crucial for critical hits which matters when you come up against higher level opponents so brute force isn't the only answer in all enagements. That alone to me is what keeps this game fresh and unique.", "hours": 87.8, "username": "dukeaearl", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 26, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-02-25", "text": "Not a Dungeon Siege game.\nDevs should go straight back to the drawing board and think of their 2 first games.\nOr straight to Jail, Dont pass GO, Do NOT collect gamers money. The Electric chair is set to warm up.\nEnd of Dungeon Siege\nThis is just a run of the mill mobile game", "hours": 0.1, "username": "CasualCoMa", "products": 48, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 27, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-22", "text": "Sacred 2, Van Helsing\nYou are part of a guild of sorts that has fallen out of favor. You learn the reasons why the crazy zealot chick wants you all dead eventually. After events take place you must fight men and monster a like and find the truth about the past or ignore it.\nThe story and atmosphere in the game are actually pretty compelling. The voice overs actually work well. The combat feels pretty good overall.\nThe game comes off with that sense that you've seen this all before. Even with a good atmosphere it never feels real. Everything is done well, but not well enough to truly hook you.\nThe game may never get you immersed and truly attached, but the story and gameplay are worth doing if your up for a solid RPG.\nIt's a solid RPG thats a bit closer to finished looking product then say Two Worlds 2, but without the engaging crafting and spells systems so I'd say $15", "hours": 0.2, "username": "blackshark64", "products": 1399, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 27, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-02-19", "text": "Terrible controls, fairly bad graphics and boring gameplay.  Give this one a wide pass at $15, and even at $3.", "hours": 0.5, "username": "HotdogWaterBurpz", "products": 248, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 27, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-02-16", "text": "Like most of my fellow here in the review section I would like to simply say, Obsidian... You \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ed up your own game series. *shakes head and frowns deeply* you have lost many lovers of these games and I would love it if you.... or hell any good game developers were to take a nice long look at the successful Dungeon Siege games *cough* not this\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665*cough* and make another so that us actual fans of the Dungeon Siege games, and world and true genre may have an \"Actual Dungeon Siege 3\"\nI write this as respectfully as I can to one of my long time favorite developers and to my fellows on steam.\nI would not and cannot recommend this half\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665attempt to milk money from your now dead series.\nEDIT: ((Allow me to ammend an error on my part... My mind is a bit muddled at the moment and because of recently playing another favorite game series of mine I spoke of Obsidian... I am actually speaking of Square Enix and it's failure in my and other's eyes to bring us, the consumers, an actual Dungeon Siege game)). Also another additive... I'm sure it's a good game if you like Action/Hack and Slash third person games and not Click to move/hack and slash RPGs with decent (though not overly great) stories.... Though I will never call this a Dungeon Siege game, as it is not. (Added in a comment to my own post, but I've now placed it here as well).", "hours": 1.7, "user_id": "76561198127575661", "username": "The Chronicler (Zagz)", "products": 48, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 27, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-02-11", "text": "The story is very mediocre, vague and kind of boring. The gameplay itself is very stiff, if you enjoy games like D3 or Torchlight you would probably hate this game.", "hours": 16.0, "user_id": "76561198009433360", "username": "Quetz", "products": 178, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 27, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-11", "text": "This has to be one of the most well done games i have played in a while. Very easy to play, and great fun. i would reccomend to people who want to be able to hack 'n slash with the ability to upgrade, loot, and level-up. super simple to grasp and easy to master 8/10", "hours": 83.9, "username": "Dasvidania Western Pig", "products": 487, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 27, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-10", "text": "I honestly don't understand the hate for this game. Honestly, I don't. This is going to be one of those short-ish reviews because, and I am sincere when I say this, there isn't a ton to say about this game that would be unique. I'm mostly going to focus on the actual in-game mechanics and aspects. I didn't play Multiplayer because, well, there is no one to play with. AFAIK, multiplayer is client-side, so you join other people's games and play as their characters and the dialogue system works in that you choose different choices and thus' you can agree/disagree with each other on what to do. It's like a voting system, I think.\nMusic : It's got some amazingly atmospheric and fitting music, as well as high quality. That's all I can say without spluring my opinionated juices all over it. You want calm forest music with birds chipping and(at least, what I heard) crickets cricketing? Well,\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 you got it. You want a creepy humming sound when in an abandoned haunted house? You got it! You want a mix of both when in the mines of a now-extinct race? Sure! For reference, go look up Stonebridge City's music. It's a perfect representation of music that fits and makes you feel \"into it\".\nStory : The game isn't really that short, according to my 22.2 hrs on record which is the fully utilized time in-game, including the DLC. So, the story itself, you ask? It was... Eh? Mediocre? Alright? Without spoiling anything, it's about the remnants of an ancient sect of an army of a long-destroyed  empire trying to fight back against a church-crazy angelic messenger. That's only the slight shortening of it. All-in-all, the story drags on a bit both because you move slowly and because it's kind of easy ot understand straight away.\nGameplay : Okay, this is where it gets kind of long and slightly \"That's just, like, your opinion, man!\" so a lot of people might disagree. I'd say that the combat / gameplay is basically Torchlight 1 / 2 but way faster-paced and with no delay between \"turns\" aka you constantly attack and have to be aware of your enemies. It's similar to Lord of the Rings : War in the North in that way. You can dodge, and it actually matters whether not you dodge, too. Especially with bullets and arrows which both move differently (bullets in a straight line, and arrows arch meaning you won't get hit if you continuously move albeit you sacrifice attacking back) as well as melee enemies. E.g. Certain enemies that lunge / jumpa at you and are unavoidable unless you dodge out of the way. Now, the thing with the dodging is that it *literally* gives you invincibility frames for the time of your dodging, meaning you can go straight through a magical missile attack (the most common champion/boss attack, to be honest) and be hurt for no damage. This makes blocking irrelevant aka USELESS, which is why using equipment that puts up block is, well, a waste of equipment.\nGraphics : This is obligatory by today's standards but, well, here it goes. It's got pretty good graphics for how well it runs on my computer, and my computer is\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 I had to run it on normal settings and it still looked amazing. Of course, the female models have your generic sexualized-esque shapely figures but I'm not one to complain. Katarina's clothing is generally stockings and corsets/loosely fitting blouses, so take that as you will. Lucas, the main tank-knight character is the ONLY person I don't like because he looks odd. It's like the default mass effect Shepard models odd. It just looks very badly done. If you're expecting a lot out of the graphics, it's no crisis or suped-up Bethesda game graphics. Don't expect a lot.\nCompanion System : I made this its own individual section because, honestly, talking about companion systems is important. Video game developers NEED to flesh them out if they're going to do them correctly, romance or no romance(which this game is the latter). The companion system works similar to Dragon Age Origins in that you get \"a point\" on your companion's like bar relationship bar(Sure, let's go with that!) whenever you say somethin they agree with. The, suprisingly happy, part about this is that you don't lose points if they don't agree with you, meaning that decision you make in dialogue effectively serve to ONLY give you points towards companion acceptance. However, this system itself only serves to add to a bonus-stat system within the game. The \"deeds\". Specifically, the companions each have their own \"deed\" to give to you per relationship level you get them to (1 per character, but you can only realistically get one to level 3, so choose wisely or balance it out, I'd choose one) and offers +X towards a stat e.g. +5 stamina. Oh, you thought there's more? No, that's it. That's literally it.  You can't even talk to your companions, they just occasionally jump in to say something when exploring or when they agree with you in conversations. This is something that developers need to work upon because this game could've had an amazing Dragon Age/Mass Effect companion system. Anjali specifically as she's amazing idea for a character and whenever she jumps in on conversations, she has hints of a hot(haha I'm so punny...?) personality in the makings.\nI may be the only person to actually care enough to make a legitimate review of this game. This game has the same curse as Dragon Age 2. Don't come in expecting a carbon-copy sequel to Dungeon Siege 1/2. Go in expecting a quick-paced Action-RPG that was clearly made to be, well, new. It is a great time-killer game in its own right. It's just not the Dungeon Siege game you were looking for. Perhaps wait for the remake, if it ever happens.", "hours": 23.6, "user_id": "76561198037427689", "username": "RobotDeathParty", "products": 707, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 27, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-08", "text": "Nice.", "hours": 21.6, "username": "Wollowon", "products": 137, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 27, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-02-07", "text": "I would gladly pay for this game again.\nIf I got the DLC for DS & DS2\nI bought this game solely on how awesome those games were\nBad decision, this is not DS3. Go play Path of Exile if you want a more recent diablo clone.", "hours": 1.4, "username": "IRON_LIZARD", "products": 243, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 27, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-03", "text": "Despite being a mediocre game, every now and then I want to play it.\nIt's fun.\n4/5", "hours": 16.3, "username": "Hate Pilot", "products": 247, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 27, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-02", "text": "I believe this game's biggest crime was naming it Dungeon Siege III. I found the game enjoyable as an action RPG-lite style game in a vein similar to the Overlord series, Dragon Age II, and perhaps Trine. Think Gauntlet and you'll be on the right track. Its a decent bit of cartoonish fantasy fun that works better with a gamepad than the traditional keyboard and mouse setup. The game features a dialogue/choice system similar to Bioware's. It's not quite as fleshed out, but not quite as pointless either. Decisions you make are neither good nor bad, just different, and will effect how things carry forth from the point they are made. With the excellent Treasure of the Sun DLC the entire game clocked in at 20 hours for the first play through including all but a few side quests. The previously mentioned choice system and four character classes lends the game a fair bit of potential replay value", "hours": 6.5, "username": "Gh0stw4r", "products": 1395, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 28, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-25", "text": "Fun game for me as a fan of the previous DS games.", "hours": 14.0, "user_id": "76561197985483054", "username": "Dandy", "products": 129, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 28, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-20", "text": "Hey look! A couch co-op RPG! That looks like it's going to be gr-...\nWhat do you mean only the host of the game keeps any progress made?", "hours": 8.7, "username": "Long-Haired Hare", "products": 243, "found_funny": 25, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 28, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-16", "text": "Years ago, I used to play the first Dungeon Siege game at LAN. Me and a friend played it a lot, never finished it, but had fun with it nonetheless. Then the second game was released, didn't play it and don't really remember why. Although, it got excited back when this third game was announced - \"Hell yeah, another game in this great series!\". Imagine the disappointment when I first played DS3 and it was NOTHING like the first two games.\nWell, that was like three years ago that I last tried DS3 and it was on the Playstation 3. One strike right there. Well, I got the game in a Humble Bundle some months back and thought I'd give it another go and surprise, surprise, I actually had a lot of fun with the game.\nThe first two games were squad based tactical RPGs, this one you're only controlling one character and you've got one companion and it's more like a Diablo clone, more than anything else. Maybe you've grown tired of Diablo 2 or 3, Titan Quest, Path of Exile... whatever it may be, and you want another game to play for a few hours (with or without friends), give DS3 a go. One character may be completed in like 10 hours and there's four to choose from so in all reality, you could play this game for abour 40-50 hours if you choose to play with all the characters.\nAnyhow, I do recommend this game but that is if you get it for a maximum of \u20ac5. So in another words, during a Steam sale or a bundle of sorts.", "hours": 10.6, "username": "disc0rd", "products": 1032, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 28, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-11", "text": "holy garbage-a-rino all i got to say bois.....owned this game since its realease thinking this was going to be the new dungeon siege but instead i paid for a terrible pile of feces. PLEASE DO NOT SPEND YOUR MONEY ON THIS GAME!!!   o.o  3:", "hours": 21.7, "user_id": "76561198000160559", "username": "ZFast", "products": 52, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 28, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-11", "text": "Excluding the issues with clunky multiplayer, not being a true Dungeon Siege game,\nthe weird gameplay, and the overall bland feeling.\nThe biggest issue with this game is a distinct lack of\nCatgirls.\nCannot recommend", "hours": 2.4, "username": "Celes Amatsu \u2605\u2112\u2134\u0475\u212f", "products": 581, "found_funny": 12, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 28, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-06", "text": "This game was pretty terrible. We went from a diablo clone (where we all knew what to expect and were fine with it), to a weird hybrid of dungeon crawler and traditional rpg. Unfortunately, the story was atrocious, so it failed in that respect. And the combat was medociore, with clunky controls. In sum: this game was a complete failure.", "hours": 14.1, "user_id": "76561198045314916", "username": "zaross1", "products": 18, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 28, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-05", "text": "if you are someone someone who has played this entire series, I do not recommend.\nThis game is nowhere near as good as the installment before this.\n(I liked it, yes, but it did not succeed the DS series at all in my eyes. better off being named something else.)\nAs for the newer players of this series, I reccomend playing this or the original first.\n-----------------------------------------------------------pros---------------------------------------------------------------\n- good story.\n- good gameplay (at least when you modify settings).\n- easier on new players.\n-----------------------------------------------------------cons---------------------------------------------------------------\n- odd default controls.\n- no wheres near as much character diversity as the 2nd.\n- too linear in challenges. (as in simple to solve problems.)\n---------------------------------------------------------summary------------------------------------------------------------\nI did enjoy this game, but the dissappointment I had with this was too high to enjoy this as much as I could have.\nI give 6/10\nif there was a neutral rating I would give it that.", "hours": 1.7, "username": "Proton Mudkip", "products": 131, "early_access": false}
