{"product_id": "39160", "page": 31, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-27", "text": "This is the worst of the 3 games in this series. The witch boss in the \"church\" is hard to beat for this 58 year old gamer.\nTried leveling up past level 20 on multiple characters and fed up with not being able to beat her.\nHad they left the game similar to the first 2 games in this series, it would have been a much better game.\nSo it is off to play something less stressful.", "hours": 22.1, "username": "SevenUp / TCA7", "products": 40, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 31, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-25", "text": "Well after beating this game, I have to say I enjoyed it. I like the combat system, most of the time it felt very skill based as opposed to just spam dps moves, you actually want to move and roll to dodge enemy attacks. I was interested in the story and ended up caring about the characters involved.  And the voice acted dialouge was nice and enoyable to listen to.\nHowever, after all that has been said, here are my complaints.....\n- Some bosses ended up feeling like bullet hells, in some cases I was almost just rolling around spamming space bar non stop while waiting for my ai componian to kill it. (especially the dlc bosses)\n- Speaking of dlc, the special moves you acquire in the dlc never felt needed.\n- The level design in the game..... sucks.....\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 just felt like narrow hallways all the way through, inside a cave? narrow hallway, outside in the open? narrow hallway, running though a town or city? narrow hallway....\n- Another thing I didn't like about the level design was during the credits I got to see the awesome concept art of each area, and it just gave me flashbacks to all the ugly textures I saw throughout the game.\n- I would say the dlc desert was the best designed since most of it felt more open and alive.\nAll in all I liked it and want to play it again with a different character, and see how the ending will change based on my decisions.", "hours": 20.2, "user_id": "76561198055002393", "username": "MegaBass", "products": 115, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 31, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-23", "text": "Terrible and boring. Made by obsidian. What else can I say. Buggy Ugly. Also perspective was terrible and dialog was painful. Even for a game that is a sequal to a hack and slash.", "hours": 17.4, "user_id": "76561198005545551", "username": "Astarsis", "products": 229, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 31, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-18", "text": "The game is tight pipe run which is \"out\" now at 2015. The game is playable after fixing the controls: wasd with move left and move right, and hold right mouse button for camera rotation. Combat is still akward: just spam click the screen without proper aiming due that I kite and dodge a lot. The view is limited in distance, giving me a closed space anxiety. Cannot view player character in detail, for screenshots. Cannot preview clothes/armor in equipment window or in shop. I succeeded to buy expensive armor that Katarina cannot wear without the game warning me prior purchase.", "hours": 3.6, "user_id": "76561198112223643", "username": "johanrainhill", "products": 137, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 31, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-15", "text": "Good story, fun gameplay. Very console-like with blockable attacks. Buggy as hell with kb+mouse: pointer disappears often, loot-all key causes a crash after a while. It's playable, but sometimes frustrating.", "hours": 35.1, "username": "Raffe", "products": 189, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 31, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-13", "text": "Forgoten phenomen.\nIt's Obsidian bug free game,\nIn the world of hack'n'slash game but with more story focused.\nWhich make it a bit strange (or bit off).\nAnd combat is more than servicable.\nBelieve or not, it's playable with kb+m (keyboard and mouse).\nThe only thing that reallly irritated me was targeting system. Pointing mouse cursor at enemy and pressing LMB, like in evey hack'n'slash, does not work every time and instead - attack something else (barrels, minions etc.).\nSome fights are unbalanced (not only for Hardcore difficulty), forced me (only once, on Hardcore mind you) to use trainer.\nI'm talking about Master Thief. You're supposed to dodge missles and focus on the boss.\nWhat you really do is rollin-rollin-rolling-rollin-die. And borked targeting system also doesn't help here...\nI count it as cRPG because it's better than other overrated AAAArpgs, but because it's Obsidian game it don't get much praise.", "hours": 44.4, "username": "NUTATCO", "products": 512, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 31, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-09", "text": "Not as good as the previous 2, but it's still not a bad game.\nCons:\n- awkware camera controls\n- slighly repetative combat\nOverall 7/10", "hours": 10.1, "username": "djschaum520", "products": 283, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 32, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-04", "text": "Not bad, though beware the dreaded \"not safe to...\" bug in chapter 4.  I've run into it on each playthrough and even using a console to try and circumvent it, I've had to restart the entire area just to advance the game. Suffice to say, this has been a known game-breaking bug since it's existence and won't likely ever get fixed (this many years later especially...).  With that caveat out of the way, it's a fun game, warts and all.", "hours": 70.1, "username": "Fye", "products": 993, "early_access": false}
