{"product_id": "39160", "page": 34, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-09-15", "text": "Really awesome story and intensive gameplay! 11/10", "hours": 32.5, "username": "CanIHelpYouSir", "products": 27, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 34, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-09-15", "text": "This is the most disappointing game ever... Dungeon Siege has always had character creation, this does NOT have it, and the way you save is REALLY lame I lose progress, Dungeon Siege 1 and 2 always had automatic save, why get rid of those most important features? And the controls are terrible, the style has changed immensly and just does not work at all.... I really tried to get into it, its way too difficult as well, potions only drop if you kill something, I mean WTF?! You cant heal, you pretty much have to do it without getting hit AT ALL... Don't waste your money buying this trash...", "hours": 4.2, "user_id": "76561198042812607", "username": "Dark J", "products": 100, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 34, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-09-10", "text": "For those who are here for a DS game can leave, for those who are here for just another game do try it out. The main reason why its getting so many negative reviews is because of this game not being like the previous DS series. It still has a great story and a decent ARPG while having good graphics. Yes there are ofcourse cons like getting used to controls and camera but if you want to say bad about this game about its bad mechanics, go try playing darksouls2 on pc without a controller >.< if you can live through the start of getting around then it really is a enjoying game.\nAll games have flaws but stop judgeing a book by its cover, just cause its a DS series game doesnt mean that if it doesnt continue the series good it stops being a game. Even most of the negative reviewers writing i quit the game in 5 mins or something still have played over 10h. HOW CAN YOU PLAY SOMETHING YOU HATE OVER 10H!?", "hours": 2.2, "user_id": "76561198041968749", "username": "Axelarate", "products": 344, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 34, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-09-05", "text": "I loved the first 2 games in this series, and despite some rough reviews of this game, I bought it at good price and I think I may have still been cheated. Not sure why they didn't let Gas Powered Games continue to do this series, but WOW!! What a mistake. This game has way too much talking going on, is way too linear (very narrow paths with no room to move), horrible camera angles, and complicated controls. Every time your guy swings, he poses for a second while he is getting whacked. You can't use all of your abilities unless you use another ability to power up some orb thing that stores it and then you can use another ability after its full. The system to change your equipment is not user friendly nor is it quick. The game stops, the screen changes, and then you make your choice. Takes way too long to do. Tehn, when you go up a level, the screen changes you to your ability screen automatically (you have no choice in this) and makes you choose right then and there. Not sure why they made it this way, but having really liked the first 2 games, this game is a total disapointment. Graphically, the games looks nice. And it looked like it could really have been a solid game if they had just stayed with what made this series good.\nProbably won't ever see another Dungeon Siege game thanks to this mess of a game and that is just sad.", "hours": 3.5, "user_id": "76561197970728391", "username": "Old Man 678", "products": 325, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 34, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-09-05", "text": "I don't understand all the negative comments. The game is quite good.", "hours": 26.7, "username": "Cinek", "products": 159, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 34, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-09-05", "text": "I put off this game for quite a while but I finally decided to play it and I enjoyed it, it's not as good as Torchlight but if you like ARPGs then you'll most likely like this one. This is more linear compared to other ARPGs but it's got a decent story, I never really played any DS games before so I can't say if this is better or worse than its predecessors. One thing I did not like was that the camera would sometimes get stuck in bad positions and was hard to see.", "hours": 12.7, "username": "R4DFIELD", "products": 417, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 34, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-31", "text": "This RPG is unique! The graphic, the characters, and couch coop! Best RPG ever!", "hours": 31.2, "username": "ForestDragon", "products": 130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 34, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-29", "text": "This game gets a lot of slack for whatever reason and I don't get it. While I didn't play the previous Dungeon Siege games, I have played a few dungeon crawlers in my day. While this one I wouldn't say is AAA good, I will say it was an enjoyable experience.\nPros:\n-Graphics\n-Unique Characters\n-Decent Combat System\n-Decent length (roughly 20 hours)\nCons:\n-The loot isn't as good as it could be\n-No way to drop items (must be sold at a shop to remove from inventory)\n-The controls without a controller feel a bit off (W,A,S,D to move instead of traditional click with the mouse to move)\n-Dialogue (while decently VA'ed), there's a little too much to go around making you want to skip it.\nOverall worthy of giving a try if you like games like Diablo, Torchlight, Titan Quest, etc.", "hours": 21.1, "username": "Stoner", "products": 285, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 35, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-26", "text": "I'm surprised by the amount of negative reviews.\nMultiple characters (with seemingly different fighting styles), nice graphics, and a well thought out story.\nYour actions have an impact on the ending making every run different enough to be interesting.\nDefinitely going back for more", "hours": 36.0, "username": "Kaushika", "products": 253, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 35, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-08-26", "text": "Lots of folks giving it negative review because it doesn't resemble the previous DS games. True, this game is vastly different then anything before. This however isn't a good argument to give this game a bad review, I even prefer games that try out something new, even if it means completely changing the game mechanics.\nThat being said, the current game has horrendous character controls, took me forever to figure out how to interact properly in combat. Lot of combat abilities used require of you to point your mouse in the direction you want them cast. In a bigger fight, with lots of mobs and numerous particle effects I'd constantly kept losing sight of pointer and would end up casting stuff in direction where there were no mobs or only a few of them. Quite frustrating. Too many stats and too generic gear that made gearing up so frustrating and a huge waste of time.\nGame storyline, while having an interesting backbone, appears to have been written by a 12 year old. While it was interesting to revisit some of the locations from original DS, the NPCs and playable characters & companions are so bleak with robot like interactions that made each convo in the game extremely cringy. You're also given an illusion of choice through dialogue, but in reality the development of events in the game aren't affected at all. These 'choices' only affect the final cutscene after you finish the game and 'influence' you gain with your companions (give you some small passive stat boosting perk).\nNow, a few things I did like is that game went in another direction. Completely revamped, you no longer drag entire army with you, instead you duo the game with one of 3 companions you get. Each companion/playable character is unique and has vastly different abilities from the other 3. This makes for an interesting experience, trying to figure out which combo is best for your play style. Also each char has two different stances, usually one for single mob fights (boss fights usually) and one for group pulls. Game also introduces transmuting and essences, which allow you to mend your gear and add one of 5 possible stats to your gear (costs a bit, but usually worth it, especially in final act of the storyline).\nMy final score for the game would be 2.5 out of 5, though you could say I'm biased. I really loved the original DS, but the 3rd installment as a standalone game isn't an RPG at all but a quickly made hack n slash, and not a good one.", "hours": 66.9, "username": "Vedran", "products": 54, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 35, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-26", "text": "Despite all the negative comments I think this is a great game. I loved the story and the gameplay. The battles, especially the boss battles, were great because you had to actually work out tactics to beat them, evade their hits and utilise  blocking.\nIf you don't want the game to be too hard you can just play it on easy. I finished it on normal playing as Lucas and thought it wasn't insanely hard. The game gives you a good challenge though.\nTo solve the camera and controller problem I changed the button layout as follows (Give it a try!) :\nW: Move Forward\nS: Move Backwards\nA: Move Left\nD: Move Right\n(And now the important bit)\nRotate Camera: Right Click\nThat way its easy to control your character and to adjust the camera angle even in busy battles", "hours": 39.0, "username": "VI", "products": 154, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 35, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-08-24", "text": "The graphics are good, the music is forgettable but in no way terrible. Clearly the story has been worked on: there seem to be quite a lot of content there. But it's wasted by the lack of choices. This is an action game before it's a RPG, and it shows: killing is your only argument and you'll then be given an choice from the unconditionnal surrender of your enemy (it gets too repetitive not to be ridiculus). Can't expect too much from a game in which all stats are combat related, and it is better than a completely linear story, just not by much.\nBut then again, this could still be a pretty darn good action game right? Well...\nThe camera controls are among the worst I've ever seen. If you play co-op like me, there's simply no choice: you have to install the command line and tweak them into something playable (it'll still be pretty bad, but at least it'll be playable). I also recommend the command line if you play in hardcore, because otherwise your damage output is too low and it takes forever to kill anything (it doesn't make things less challenging, just less boring).\nI had to start a new game because I started with Lucas, the melee character, and it became apparent that my damage was so low it wasn't worth hitting enemies and blocking (although it's very effective) was useless because I didn't have any 'taunt' skill.\nCombat is repetitive. I've seen this game compared to Diablo, with people not understanding how the two games are similar. Well, Diablo's combat (considered very repetitive by many) is LESS repetitive than this game's, and there's a simple reason for that: in Diablo, your character's skills make your gameplay vary, making you want to level up to get new mechanics. In comparison, DS III would actually benefit from not having levels, as very few skills introduce new mechanics. Indeed, it would have been better to put the skills on equipement, which is otherwise just a collection of numbers (there's no unique effects) added to your character's attack.\nThe simple combat mechanics of the game aren't too bad though, just don't play if you don't have a controller. There's just one attack button (with a 3 attacks loop), no combo system, a nice dodge system (by far the best part of this game, IMHO). The two stances mechanic was a good attempt at varying the gameplay, but it's ruined by the loot system: if you get a good item for one stance, the other becomes pretty much useless.\nI'm not sure the game was play tested for its gameplay, as we found ourselves with way too much money effortlessly and yet nothing to spend it on, despite having bad equipement.\nThe only bug we encountered (a door preventing the main character from going to the boss room, effectively blocking any progress until we cheated our way in) was caused by the camera tweak, so I don't have any complain there.", "hours": 16.4, "username": "Raksura", "products": 76, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 35, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-08-23", "text": "This game  goes into a darn near no win situation on the first boss. If you love being frustrated in less than one hour of gameplay than by all means buy this game. I REGRET BUYING IT NOW AND WILL NOT RECOMEND THIS GAME AT ALL. But then again thats probably why it is so cheap now. What a waste of money!!!!!!!!!!!!!!", "hours": 1.7, "user_id": "76561197978537241", "username": "vance333", "products": 63, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 35, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-23", "text": "Cause who doesn't like a good dungeon crawler? This game has loot, skills, specializations, different classes and more. Without having played the previous Dungeon Siege titles, this one just felt like an old classic along the lines of Champions of Norrath. This is a great game for the price. Don't expect Diablo 3 level graphics or skill animations, but it keeps things simple while also offering decent variety.\nRecently tried the multiplayer. You can join your friends very easily, or play with strangers if you want to. It's annoying that you can't save your character if you join a friend, but the game saves that character for you so you keep the abilities and gear that you collect. Still, very fun to play with a friend and a great game in my opinion.", "hours": 12.1, "user_id": "76561198079602090", "username": "Chronic Crystal", "products": 373, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 35, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-21", "text": "+ Smooth combat\n+ Nice character designs\n+ Great storyline\n+ Nice map system\n- Very dizzy camera\n- No Create-a-Character system\nThis is a very good game overall, however it's so different from Dungeon Siege I & II that it shouldn't be named Dungeon Siege III. Maybe Dungeon Siege: Retribution or something like that? IMO one of the main reasons this game gets so much hate is because, the way it was named generated a lot of expections from long time fans of the franchise.\nHonestly this game is very decent to say the least, so try it if you don't mind that the gameplay is different than the previous two DSs.\n7/10", "hours": 0.4, "username": "Ty", "products": 510, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 35, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-21", "text": "more than a nice game!", "hours": 1.0, "username": "RFsoufi", "products": 13, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 35, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-20", "text": "This game is much harder the Diablo 3.  Sure, Diablo 3 has more chaos and effects on-screen, but it just isn't that demanding in terms of tactics (unless you go up several Torment levels).  Dungeon Siege III demands that you react quickly and use both fightings modes with their associated abilities properly.\nBut beware, just like Diablo, there's a bit of grinding involved, especially if you want better gear.\nBasically, if you like Diablo 3 but wish it required a little more skill, then I highly recommend Dungeon Siege III.", "hours": 16.5, "username": "ihvahn", "products": 326, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 35, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-20", "text": "I normally dont post that many reviews but sense this game has gotten so many negative reviews i feel i should post a positive one. I just got this game on sale and  ilove it. I would have been fine with paying full price for it. It seems most of these negative reviews are from people who have played the first 2 games. I have not. I bought the second one when i bought this but i wanted to play this one first.\nI have been looking for a solid RPG that was not as in depth and time consumming as WOW or Skyrim and i am so happy i found this game, cant wait to start the second one.", "hours": 45.3, "user_id": "76561198049946694", "username": "jasonb8419", "products": 193, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 36, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-08-18", "text": "If your looking for a game that resembles the mechanics found in Dungeon Siege 1 & 2 this is NOT the game for you. You are limited into a class based on which of the 4 pre-made characters you pick at the start of the game. All the customization and freedom found in the other Dungeon Siege games is missing here. it is a simplified game, Which is not what i was looking for in a Dungeon Siege game.", "hours": 2.8, "username": "Jabbic", "products": 343, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 36, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-17", "text": "I love this game!  I haven't played Dungeon Siege I or II so I can't compare this one to the previous ones.  I highly recommend playing this game with an Xbox controller, or something simlilar, because it is literally a game changer.  Playing with a controller seems to make the gameplay more fluid.", "hours": 21.2, "username": "ritterkraft", "products": 217, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 36, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-17", "text": "If you are a fan of the series, this will not dissapoint.", "hours": 30.4, "user_id": "76561198024930612", "username": "violentstreak", "products": 657, "early_access": false}
