{"product_id": "39160", "page": 40, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-24", "text": "After playing this game for quite some time I have found the game to be very functional dungeon crawler that combines support and co-op aspects.  I'm pleased with the end result and have found the single player experience to be very good and entertaining.  It is unfortunate that multiplayer does not allow you to carry over your earned items.  You will have to play someone else's character.  It's a pain.  But great game none the less.", "hours": 48.1, "username": "MajorDragoon1991", "products": 463, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 40, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-11", "text": "Most of the negative reviews for this game are about it not being similar to the previous games and being a vastly different experience in the Dungeon Siege series. I've never played the first two games myself, however, even if I did, I would still believe Dungeon Siege III is a really good game. I would describe Dungeon Siege III as something that could be a Dragon Age action RPG spin-off.\nTell you what, try the demo and decide whether you want to buy it or not. If you are familiar with the Dungeon Siege games, try playing the third one again. You may actually like it, or not. Give it an hour or two. It could be a whole different game, but you know, if you enjoy playing it as much as I do, then it's a good game to you as much as it is to me.", "hours": 17.8, "username": "dongis", "products": 861, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 40, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-03", "text": "PROS:\n1. Great story/lore\n2. Your decisions shape the story/relationships with other characters\n3. Great graphics/music/voice acting\n4. Maps are easy to follow\n5. Trail feature allows you to see where you need to go for a quest\n6. Seamless changeable battle stances\n7. Point and click facing enemies rather than mindless one-click automation (More engaging battles)\n8. Learning about a set character's backstory and personality (Refreshing change from spending a lot of time customizing a character yourself)\n9. Easy to follow/understandable/simple talent tree (Refreshing change from tedious, complicated talent trees)\nCONS:\n1. TERRIBLE camera angles / control. I mean it was so bad, I almost didn't want to play this game.\n2. No zooming in feature.\n3. Playing as Lucas is darn near impossible. You're in for a huge challenge if you decide to play as him.\n4. This game has near NOTHING to do with the first two games, therefore making it more of its own game rather than a continuation to the series.\nI felt like I owed this game my two cents because honestly I'm astonished at the amount of bad reviews. I will fully admit to this: After I first bought the game I only played it for one hour before giving up in frustration. The camera control in this game is absolutely TERRIBLE. If they would have just made it so the camera follows the way the character is facing, it would have solved the problem entirely. I also hated the fact I can't zoom in at all, because I like to look at my character and the monster detail closely on occasion. Despite this, I decided to give the game another chance later on because I am a huge fan of the Dungeon Siege series and I really wanted to finish the third installment. Getting used to the stupid camera controls took a lot of patience but eventually I found I had almost shrugged off an awesome game. The lore and storyline is rich and engaging, arguably the best aspect of this game. I also really enjoy how my decisions shape the game's outcomes and relationships with the other playable characters, much like The Walking Dead series (which I also love). The graphics and music are great, the voice acting is excellent. I liked how the maps were easy to follow and I almost never got lost due to the really great quest trail feature. Being able to swap between \"stances\" or whatever you want to call them during battle was near seamless. I actually liked that you had to point and click in the direction of the enemy rather than mindlessly clicking once on a target and letting your character attack by themselves as in DS1 and DS2(that is, if you choose the DS1 style of doing that when playing DS2). Many will argue that just having four generic characters is boring and un-inventive on the player's part - however I personally feel it is a refreshing change. You get to uncover this character's rich backstory, and learn their personality and style as you play. It's almost like getting to know a new friend rather than just making up a fake one. lol. Besides, I could spend upwards of 1-2 hours fully customizing my character down to the shape of her nose (*cough* Elder Scrolls anyone?) and for what? She's going to be wearing a helmet anyway, and even if you have a mod to make it so you can see your character's face, how often are you actually going to look at it? It ends up being kinda tedious, especially since I just want to get onward to the game! I -would- have liked to at least be given the choice of keeping their generic name OR coming up with my own like some RPGs, but meh it's not a game-changer for me either. As for other things I DON'T like about this game, let's talk about Lucas for a second. I'm a straight girl, so when I saw Lucas I was like wow this guy looks super hot...I'm going to try him out. ;P BIG mistake. The problem with Lucas is that to do any real damage you have to basically be up the enemy's \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, and when you're in the process of doing that in a huge mass of flustercuck you're going to get mowed down as often as the White House lawn. Unless you fully specced into every healing ability possible and have a ton of chaos:vampirism as Lucas, then you're in for a world of pain my friend. I don't really like when a game forces me to spend all my talent currency in ONE thing. Like okay well if I don't want to die over and over and over again I better spend everything in every healing ability possible. Super lame! My favorite character has got to be Katarina. Her gear looks cute and girly, her voice actress sounds exotic and awesome, and she hits like a truck from afar. I can just sit back and send my cool hound in while doing some badarse sniping and when the enemy gets too close I can just switch to my sidearms and deal powerful knockback damage. Amazing. Anjali is also fricken AWESOME. She's absolutely beautiful, especially in her fire form with all those tribal tattoos and the orange eyes. The way they made her voice actress (as well as the other archon in the game) sound all ethereal-ish was cool as hell too, it really added depth to the exotic element of her race. Her fire jackal is super cute, I love the little noises he makes!! Her self-healing is ridiculously through the roof, it's almost impossible to die as her if you do it right. She also has some decent range on her attacks, and both of her forms are viable though I tend to stick more to her fire form. Reinhart is the only one I haven't tried yet and meh, I probably won't. For some reason whenever I look at him I think of the Sultan from Aladdin and I start laughing. Also the way he talks is kind of annoying. lol. I've never even used him as the AI. I'm sure he's a great character with great abilities if I just gave him the chance, but meh. Moving on, I see a lot of people complaining about the very basic talent tree but let me tell you something, I WELCOMED it. Huge, complicated talent trees with a billion different avenues has always been one of the things I actually DON'T like about RPGs. It's like, here let me google online what is the very best talent tree and fricken -research- how to play my dang character. Otherwise I'm going to be halfway through a game and realize shoot I totally screwed up my talent tree and I can't go back so now I either keep playing and pretend it doesn't bother me or restart. GROAN. It's like work instead of play at that point! In closing, I see a lot of the angry people are commenting that they don't like this game simply because it isn't like the other two. True, it IS sort-of a letdown that this game has next-to-nothing similar with the first two games other than some very minor basic lore ties. But I wouldn't just throw out the whole thing just because it isn't a similar or because it \"shames the franchise\". I tend to want to look at it as its own game...just ignore the whole continuation of the 3 slapped onto the name. :P", "hours": 17.1, "user_id": "76561198073491321", "username": "SpookyEmily", "products": 49, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 41, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-05-03", "text": "Bought this game for $2 because I loved DS 1 and DS 2.\nI feel like I wasted $2. I played it for 30 minutes and it was enough. The story is boring, the camera controls are horrible, the assets are copy paste, the gameplay is just bad. Also, everything that was good about dungeon siege is just gone.\nMaybe it's a good game for $2 if you never tried DS before, but if you did, it's just a huge disapointment and overall a terrible game.", "hours": 0.2, "username": "Von Mackensen", "products": 410, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 41, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-05-02", "text": "Streamlined version of the previous games. Set in the same world, but almost nothing similar to the previous games.", "hours": 35.1, "username": "Want|Some", "products": 503, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 41, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-04-30", "text": "This game is OK, but if you are looking for a game like the first two, then DON'T buy this game. It's like they made a completely different game and slapped on the name Dungeon Siege III.", "hours": 61.0, "user_id": "76561198044320684", "username": "Finn128", "products": 332, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 41, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-27", "text": "I gather that the Dungeon Siege fanbase for the first two games looks down on Dungeon Siege 3 as a departure from the very enjoyable gameplay motif. But I never played those two games. I started with Dungeon Siege 3, and it's not really half bad. The combat can get stale and the looting isn't as enjoyable as say Diablo or Titan Quest, and if you buy the game with the Treasures of the Sun DLC you'll get powerful items that will easily carry you through the rest of the game. The redeeming value in this adventure is the story and its lore, but if you're not the kind of gamer that enjoys that sort of thing, then you can skip this one.\nFor me, I enjoyed trekking mindlessly from quest to quest (with zero exploration since you can summon a path with the press of a button) piecing together the game world and its history.\nI'd recommend it for someone seeking an easy RPG to play that's something other than Diablo. Watch my full review below:", "hours": 20.2, "username": "Theje", "products": 419, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 41, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-22", "text": "DS 3 is quite differeent to DS1 and DS2 with characters that feel more real. This is also the game Dragon Age copied from", "hours": 24.0, "username": "ziplock9000", "products": 176, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 41, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-04-19", "text": "The most important thing you need to know if you think this might be nice game to play with friends is that the camera makes this game unplayable in multiplayer!  Not difficult to play UNPLAYABLE, it feeling like playing gauntlet for PS1 on a 10 inch TV.\nIf you want a below average action RPG the is single player ONLYyou might consider this for $1, no more.  However if you wanted any game that even slightly resembled the other games in this series, run as far from this game as you can.", "hours": 4.4, "user_id": "76561197980999216", "username": "Red Sniper", "products": 408, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 41, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-04-16", "text": "Possibly the WORST PC game I have ever played.  The controls are bad, the progression is worse.  It's a shame because I played and enjoyed Dungeon Siege I and II.  I do not recommend, not at all.", "hours": 13.4, "username": "Ookabea", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 41, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-16", "text": "I have never played a game where I fell in love with all of the charactors before. I also never wanted a game to last longer then it did. Hands down the best rpg I have played in a LONG time.", "hours": 56.1, "user_id": "76561198036252595", "username": "ffiore89", "products": 105, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 41, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-10", "text": "IT a  great game but wish it hads  cheat code's  to help out in hrad part and could ues mre set up on how fine thing and what can ues in game but over all it great game", "hours": 5.8, "user_id": "76561198205710420", "username": "Daniel", "products": 29, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 41, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-04-08", "text": "It supports co-op, but player #2 can't save their games. It's pretty stupid. Too bad that the DS series has fallen so far - I have fond memories of DS1 and DS2 but this was really dumbed down so it could be ported to consoles. Avoid this game.", "hours": 14.9, "username": "Rectus Dominus", "products": 222, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 42, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-04-05", "text": "Don't let my playtime fool you, I've got 4-5 hours logged in this game across accounts, consoles, and demo.  I only own it because the entire Dungeon Siege trilogy was on sale.\nIt's an awful, awful third installment of what was once a great series.  Camera controls are terrible, gameplay is simplistic in the worst possible ways -- this turned Dungeon Siege from a wonderfully atmospheric party-based RPG to a thoughtless button-mashing ARPG.  A sad end to the franchise.\nIf you're looking for an updated version of DS1 or DS2 to play, this is not it.  Go back to DS2 and try to sort out the multiplayer bugs instead.\nI have heard the couch multiplayer in this is acceptable, though I have not tried it.", "hours": 0.6, "username": "Blue_J", "products": 256, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 42, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-04-03", "text": "its only single player", "hours": 0.5, "user_id": "76561198097538827", "username": "Maurasame", "products": 130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 42, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-01", "text": "I loved this game, despite the combat being overly repetitive and not too interesting. I guess I'm just a sucker for these style of rpgs. I'd recommend to anyone to at least give it a playthrough.", "hours": 25.6, "user_id": "76561198039513393", "products": 22, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 42, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-31", "text": "Terrible, dumbs down what was at one point an awesome series.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561197971326684", "username": "null_ref", "products": 385, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 42, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-31", "text": "I haven't played the first two of this series, and the only similar game I can compare it to is Blizzard's Diablo. In comparison to that I find this game to be acceptable. The way some negative reviews go on about the lack of story and horrible gameplay mechanics, you would think they are comparing it to Baldur's Gate. The earlier Dungeon Siege games have never been compared to Baldur's Gate so I'm assuming they are nowhere as complex and engaging. With that in mind this game in itself may not be a great RPG, nor an improvement over the older series installments, but it's a decent game that I would recommend to other Diablo players who prize gameplay over plot.\nAlso, the camera controls are fully customizable so if a player has issues with it, they must be the type of player who only plays on default settings. I never play on default so my game plays how I want it.", "hours": 22.5, "user_id": "76561197970520668", "username": "Medereyes", "products": 138, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 42, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-30", "text": "I have beat this game and it's DLC and have completed every side quest in this game. Only play this game if you want to play single player.\nIn short, If you want a co-op rpg DONT PLAY THIS GAME. It has one of the worst versions of multiplayer i have ever seen in a game. The game forces both players into the same screen (which for pc is a slap in the face), only the host of the game gets to progress any character, money spend is the hosts money, any items obtained are only obtained for teh host, If you have a mic plugged in its always on (no toggle to talk) and etc. Overall its pretty much pointless to play multiplayer unless you own it on console and only play with a friend at your house.\nIf you are reading this you most likely dont care about multiplayer or realize that the game has been out for so long that the multiplayer base (what little there was) is now dead. Honestly i have to say that the single player aspects in this game are fantastic. While in single player you are limited to only 1 additional teammate. Depending on play style will depend on who you like to partner with the most. The story line is the thing that suprised me the most. Unlike mass effect your decisions often effect you long term. For example early in the game you get the choice of killing an archon, putting her in jail, or letting her go free. While the first choice will give you an extremely powerfull staff for that level, it will in turn make all future instances with archons hate you forever.\nThe combat is what i really enjoy most about this game. Each character you have has 3 abilities and 2 stances that they can switch between totaling 6 abilities overall. Each stance is either single target is aoe focused. Each stance though often has buffs or pets you can summon that remain active even if you switch. So reguardless of the situation i often found myself switching between them fairly often just to get the extra buff out even if that stance wasn't optimal. Using its combat system took a little to get use to. It's a small delay but deals quite a bit of dmg if you are able to get combo hits off or finish a long casting spell.", "hours": 55.7, "user_id": "76561197981181435", "username": "Moondude", "products": 252, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 42, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-29", "text": "What do you have to do most in this game? Fight! And thats the most boring part of the game.", "hours": 1.4, "user_id": "76561198036382087", "username": "cereal killer", "products": 247, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 42, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-25", "text": "Pretty good game.\nI've played Dungeon Siege II before - and I can say Dungeon Siege III is better for me.\n8/10", "hours": 17.1, "username": "nx2", "products": 43, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 42, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-23", "text": "my god what have they done to this game......catastrophic faliure!!!!", "hours": 2.2, "user_id": "76561198015832343", "username": "uBiCa", "products": 168, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 42, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-22", "text": "The story is utter bullcrap. Jeyne Kassynder, a heroine, who freed the land from tyrants and royals, is made here a villain and asked the players to be fought against. What the f***? I would play for Jeyne and slay remaining filth of the legion and the hiding royals (and wipe out the remaining Montbarron line), BUT YOU CAN NOT! So basically you are asked to be bad guy in this game and hunt down rebel Robin Hood. Makes no sense.... but then again there are games where you are terrorist and r@pist and general bad guy (GTA series)... - this game is sadly one of those.\nNow about the gameplay annoyances:\n1. The game is either locked into fullscreen or when you disable it, the mouse is trapped into the game window - what the f***? THERE IS NO OPTION TO MAKE THE GAME RUN IN BORDERLESS WINDOW MODE! :-(\n2. If you have controlled attached to your computer, but are not using it - so better unplug it and restart the game or you're f***ed. As the keybindings are just simply ignored when you had active controller plugged in when you started the game. NO WAY TO DISABLE CONTROLLER IN-GAME! :-(\n3. the few story clips here are there seem to be in 640x480 resolution, streched over your screen... so you can see the huge jaggy squares. BAD QUALITY STORYLINE VIDEOS!\n4. Anjali character in her fire elemental form takes damage while being in fire.... WHAT THE F***? (NO LOGIC; NO COMMON SENSE!)\n5. Anjali in her elemental form has no nipples and no pubic hair flaming around like her head-hair does. Game is PEGI-16, so there should be no problem with those even for PEGI reasons. ANATOMICALLY INCORRECT!\n6. Tutorials about using different fighting abilities jump up during the fight without pausing the fight, so you have to fast close them to survive and fight off the attacking monsters without being even able to read what was written there. BAD USER INTERFACE!", "hours": 1.5, "username": "deemon", "products": 1903, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 43, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-21", "text": "One of the best isometric action games there is. Definitely a really good game. Four playable classes, my fav being the mage because he has cool looking spells like clockwork bombs. I have beaten the game with him and the entire game was awesome. Now I am playing the dlc Treasures of the Sun with my gunner. The gunner can switch between a rifle and dual wielded weapons that include a one handed shotgun and pistol and she has some really powerful skills. The fighter chick can summon a fire dog to help and the warrior is pretty self explanatory with some good skills also. The voice acting is very good and the game has memorable sound effects. The mouth movement actually matches the words in most cases in cut scenes. That's some pretty good detail for a top-down action game. The music is superb and always fitting of the place and mood. The graphics are really very good and hold up very well even by today's standards. The best thing about the game is its unique combat system. You get two sets of weapons with three skills each, and you can hold right trigger to activate more powerful versions of your spells or hold left trigger to activate healing and defensive skills. Obviously I play with a xbox 360 controller and it actually works very well because otherwise I would never even consider using a controller for a isometric game. A good example of a game that you can easily find somewhere on sale for a steal or could actually pay its regular price of $15 and that is still a great price, especially since the game will give you around 14-16 hours of playtime as it did me.\n8/10 one of my all-time favs.", "hours": 17.2, "username": "Hurtbringer", "products": 1148, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 43, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-20", "text": "very fun game. reminds me of van helsing on steam.very nice graphics too.", "hours": 1.9, "username": "NeoGeoMVS", "products": 420, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 43, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-18", "text": "Dungeon Siege III needs a makeover it nothing like 1 or2  fun to play free roaming maps bring them back, if they ever bring another one out i will not buy it if it not like the first 2 please bring back the fun in co-op gaming", "hours": 44.8, "user_id": "76561197970799254", "username": "JimJukem", "products": 336, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 43, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-15", "text": "I am astounded. DS1, DS2, and then this? We were lied to. I don't care how many other ways you want to cover up that fact, but welcome to the business marketing world (psychological warfare). It had the name DS3 simply to sell it--grub some more cash. I have played maybe 10 minutes of this game, and I will not waste anymore of my time on it.\nI am angry enough that Dungeon Siege 1 and 2 are not multiplayer-able in Steam (someone should definitely be locked up for that, all by itself). Dungeon Siege 3 was a marketing lie. Lock this guy up. He had done some careless, selfish things with his merchandise, and should be slapped. I don't care how many people on here say, \"Der, this is not like DS 1 and 2, but-but-but... it's the best game I've ever played! It's an amazing ARPG!!\" --- Baloney and cheese, that's what that is.\nHe failed, and should not get any attention. He should care more about his audience and gamers than this. He deserves the failure he received from trying to make a \"console\" game, and not being faithful to his gamers and followers he had. Fluffy-fluff.", "hours": 0.3, "username": "N1TE3YE", "products": 55, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 43, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-08", "text": "Clunky Interface.  Not nearly as good as I or II.", "hours": 0.9, "user_id": "76561197971942267", "username": "ebmogensen", "products": 52, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 43, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-08", "text": "If you're a fan of Dungeon Siege 1, stay away from this one.\n- No character customization\n- No class building as you play. You pick a class at start\n- All picked up items look the same\n- No inventory! <- Big let down for me.\nThis game is so bad, I am avoiding all Square Enix games now!", "hours": 2.8, "user_id": "76561197971470922", "username": "Daivuk", "products": 150, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 43, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-06", "text": "I honestly loved this game it was another great instalment to the Dungeon Siege game only down side is no pack mule *pout*. other than that i really dont have any complaints about the game i also love the ability to use a controler with this game. the only downside is some times it can lag out depending on the computer. Awsome graphics and a good user interface makes this game worth buying expecially if your a fan of these types of rpgs.", "hours": 27.7, "user_id": "76561198060681929", "username": "ladyintheshadows", "products": 75, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 43, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-05", "text": "A fair adventure game with great graphics and environments, good voice acting and decent story largely ruined by a horrible camera angle which will have many ranged enemies shooting you from off screen and many ranged attacks by your characters hitting enemies you can't even see.\nAn additional frustration is enemies respawning in areas you've already cleared.   This happens despite times in the story where you are blocking off entrances to areas to prevent that exact thing!  Combat is also a little too simplified to really be enjoyable.\nA beautiful game that just misses too many marks and has an enjoyment killing flaw.", "hours": 17.2, "user_id": "76561197972607142", "username": "g4ng", "products": 445, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 43, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-04", "text": "Yes ..this is a wonderful game .. but its not the same as the old ones .. so missed the mark there .. but otherwise its very good !!!", "hours": 9.7, "user_id": "76561198083819984", "username": "ninnasontse", "products": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 43, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-04", "text": "Good game", "hours": 51.6, "user_id": "76561198076210446", "username": "FallenAngel", "products": 160, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 44, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-02", "text": "I tried... i really tried but the game is utterly horrible. Please do not support a game like this. I got it for free and I still am annoyed that I even spent time on it.\nPlusses: Graphics are ok... for a year 2008 game.\nMinuses:\nControls. They are propably worst I`ve ever played with.\nCamera angles, they dont show the enemies which shoot  you from otherside of the room etc.\nCamera controls, you have to rotate the camera while moving, shooting, doing spells etc... Really doesnt work.\nRpg-elements are none existing. You honestly cannot really customize your character when compared to any other even mediocre ARPG or RPG.\nStory is bad... it has no life  in it.\nCharacters in game have zero personality.\nEnemies are the same... over and over again.", "hours": 15.5, "user_id": "76561197991239902", "username": "Mauseleum", "products": 125, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 44, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-27", "text": "Because of reasons", "hours": 2.6, "username": "Mutters03hnchen | joker", "products": 202, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 44, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-27", "text": "I can recommend this game. I got it for $5 with the DLC.\nIts a good hack and slash romp. I have no idea what is has to do with DS1 and 2 but that didnt stop it being fun.\nI really do recommend having a game controller to play it as it was designed with consoles in mind.", "hours": 26.7, "user_id": "76561198037126760", "username": "Dumbarse", "products": 131, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 44, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-26", "text": "Loved it, great game.", "hours": 16.7, "username": "SouthScout", "products": 164, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 44, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-25", "text": "If you're looking to scratch that hack and slash itch like the previous Dungeon Siege games did, this is not the game to do it with. At first, I was very disappointed by that. However, once I got over that I actually enjoyed it quite a bit.\nWhile the gameplay is mediocre, the voice acting, graphics, story, and lore are all fantastic.", "hours": 30.5, "user_id": "76561198048568021", "username": "Fitzch", "products": 85, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 44, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-22", "text": "This game is great!  I got it on a sale because I've heard good things about the series for over a decade.  I never really got into the other games, but I bought this one because I noticed that it was done by Obsidian.  I'm glad I did because I really enjoyed this game. The story isn't anything great, but it works for the game.  The gameplay is where I had the most fun.  It's not complicated at all.  The simplicity of this game is really great because I don't always want to get my\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665kicked by every game I play.  It was really enjoyable just to enjoy the fun story and gameplay without all of the micromanagement of Diablo or similar games.  The game is totally worth the price especially if it comes on sale.", "hours": 15.4, "user_id": "76561198066348512", "username": "DoctorSushi", "products": 224, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 44, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-22", "text": "The game curve was just horible, from going to easy as hell to so hard it makes you want to throw your computer at the wall it was just awful.\nPlus the fact you could not customise your characters, I don't know if this was just lazyness or just complete lack of respect for the people who played through this game series.", "hours": 2.6, "username": "justinverigin", "products": 89, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 44, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-22", "text": "This game sucks! All your chacrtor does is die, die, die,die,die,die,die,die,die,die,die,die,die,die,die,die,die,!!!!!!!!!!!", "hours": 15.1, "user_id": "76561197983874919", "username": "randalllee", "products": 69, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 44, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-21", "text": "Decent game, but I think this game is NOT-SO-DUNGEON-SIEGE~", "hours": 1.6, "username": "Mister Troglodyte", "products": 124, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 44, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-21", "text": "Very linear game play, not much character evolution, dry story line. the second game was much better.", "hours": 20.4, "user_id": "76561198037609421", "username": "Mercenary584", "products": 64, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 45, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-20", "text": "Although both story and presentation leave something to be desired, there's something about the gameplay that kept me motivated to play through the whole thing. In Co-Op it's even pretty fun.", "hours": 51.2, "username": "Maguro Man", "products": 528, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 45, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-19", "text": "Picked this up on sale - I am a huge Dungeon Siege 2 fan, as well as a fan of hack and slash RPGs.\nI really tried liking this game, but I couldnt. Graphics were good, but beyond that I cant recommend any aspect of this game.", "hours": 4.6, "username": "I immediately regret my decision", "products": 354, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 45, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-17", "text": "While this game may be a far cry from it's predecessors, it's still a decent game in it's own right. Story is pretty decent and entertaining enough to keep me interested. The mouse controls are horrendous though and I recommend playing this with some sort of controller.", "hours": 6.9, "username": "mihnt", "products": 164, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 45, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-16", "text": "Short version: This is a competent and enjoyable \"Diablo clone\". Certainly worth the time\nIt has some interesting places, a story decent enough you don't just roll your eyes and quit it (Yes, that would be you, Lords of Shadow. Yours didn't last 3 maps). It has a lot of what I emember being optional content and nice mechanics. Guess a testament to how well it was made is that I finished it once and still wanted to have another go with a different character AND see how it plays out with a party. So yeah.. worth the monies, worth the times, would play it again (especially now it's been quite a while and I've forgot most details)", "hours": 27.3, "username": "Vile Lasagna", "products": 360, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 45, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-16", "text": "This is not dungeon siege. This is just a plain boring action game where u spam attacks and slash through meat bags.\nThis is some random action game that apparently has a name label dungeon siege on it.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561198001960141", "username": "[RGDT]Phadthai", "products": 104, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 45, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-15", "text": "One of my favorite games of all time.\nAn action RPG (more RPG than ARPG, you mind), with an in-deapth storyline and good loot tables. They did a fantastic job with the atmosphere of each area, capturing the feeling of darkness and turmoil in each zone while keeping the individuality of each location.\nThe combat is challenging, and each playable character brings a feeling of uniqueness to the combat. The followers add support that (at times) is much needed. The loot system is decent, and upgrades feel exciting. Watching your gear change as you gain levels is as satisfying as it is in any other well-done ARPG.\nAs long as you're not looking to play this game with friends, you'll find DS3 to be a well-rounded, immersive game with a storyline that will suck you right in.", "hours": 82.4, "username": "Jarl Hamm", "products": 2132, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 45, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-14", "text": "A lot of people\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665and moan about this game in the reviews, and I can understand why. The game plays nothing like either of the first two titles, and is quite restricted in what you can customize about your character. That aside this is a really damned fine RPG, and the story is very much equal to the other Dungeon Siege titles. Available quests and in game lore pay a great deal of tribute to those titles as well. The biggest complaint I have for this one is the camera is really restricted in how far you can move it and zoom, there are a couple quick fixes available on the net that will remove this though, and that makes the game much better by itself. Locations and characters are quite beautifully done, and the voice acting is very good. The only real negative to this game is that the story cut scenes are basically poorly drawn stills with narration.", "hours": 29.2, "user_id": "76561198116745143", "username": "Tyrranus", "products": 145, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 45, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-14", "text": "Graphically beautiful but with clunky controls. Dungeon Siege III is a vast departure from the long in depth story of Dungeon Siege 1 + 2. Dungeon Siege III is a focused linear story line played in cutscene and with quick gameplay. The characterization is well done but of the 4 player character choices it is clear that Lucas and Anjali have the advantage. A decent hack and slash for the 6-10 hours it would take to finish.  Worth the purchase on Steam Sale if you are looking for an experience similar to  Diablo a time constraint.", "hours": 3.6, "user_id": "76561198006568226", "username": "Pyrus", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 45, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-14", "text": "Not sure why so many people be hating on this game. I was a die hard fan of DS1 and I really enjoyed this game. They bring in all the lore from the first one. It is 150 years later, but the story line is still great. I'm assuming that any bad reviews are coming from people who havent played more than an hour of the game or really suck at the new gameplay. They just a bunch of pansies. It does take some pratice to work the camera and hotkeys properly, but once you do it is easy to enjoy the game. I played as Katarina my first time through and had no problems once I figured everything out. The more melee style characters may be more difficult. I was definitely more disappointed with DS2. This one was a nice surprise, I went in expected to be disappointed. Definitely is an underrated game. I recommend you give it a chance.", "hours": 28.9, "user_id": "76561198032572410", "username": "Fish n Chimps", "products": 20, "early_access": false}
