{"product_id": "39160", "page": 47, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-02", "text": "If you have enjoyed playing dungeon siege and dungeon siege 2 then I do not recommend this one. HUGE disappointment.  The story was decent but gameplay was terrible. Trying to maneuver character and fight was almost impossible. Cannot emphasize enough how disappointing this game is.", "hours": 11.3, "user_id": "76561198036644094", "username": "roachybelle", "products": 8, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 47, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-01", "text": "I attempted to play the first Dungeon Siege game, but I couldn't get into it, so I decided to play this one first. From what I played, you don't have to know what happend prior to this game since there are plenty of lore books lying around to read to get caught up.\nI tried playing with a mouse and keyboard initially, but felt weird to play and a little complicated. So I tried playing with a gamepad controller and the game became much better and enjoyable.\nThis game was meant to played with a controller, not a mouse and keyboard. PLAY with a controller.", "hours": 27.1, "user_id": "76561197972328095", "username": "LoneHail", "products": 866, "early_access": false}
