{"product_id": "39160", "page": 49, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-12", "text": "1. PLAY THIS GAME WITH CONTROLLER! NOT WITH KEYBOARD + MOUSE\n2. I don't know why this game called Dumgeon Siege. Its not. Nothing like DS, DS2, Diablo, etc.\n3. Great game for the fans of Baldur's Gate: Dark Alliance and such.\n4. Nice art, solid world and lore, simplistic, but fun battle system.\n5. PLY THIS GAME WITH CONTROLLER!!!\nWant another DS game? DS3 is not for you. Want nice simple action RPG? This game is for you.", "hours": 19.6, "username": "Gemanoneko", "products": 1154, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 49, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-01-09", "text": "Nothing like the original two, played a couple hours of it and wish i could refund... 3/10", "hours": 4.6, "username": "THEBIGDICKBANDIT", "products": 108, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 49, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-01-07", "text": "Don't let the pretty graphics and promos fool you: This is NOT the DS you know or remember. Dungeon Siege 3 is more like a horribly failed attempt at a Gauntlet game. If you can stomach the game past the first few levels then I think it lets you use more than one ability. This one is astonishingly bad, steer clear!", "hours": 0.1, "username": "NERO", "products": 187, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 49, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-07", "text": "Absolutely great hack'n'slash action game. Pleasant graphics, interesting characters, great atmoshere and an ok story, but most importantly - the gameplay is very dynamic and thrilling and, even though it's quite simple and repeateative, like of any action-RPG, it doesn't ever tire, cause consecution of fights, exploring and dialogs is designed so that nothing feels too excessive.\nThe difficuly is made most perfectly: challenging (totally insane on hardcore, I advise against playing it solo), yet no cheap pish like stunlocks, unavoidable blows, invincible enemies and QTE, so loved by nowadays developers. Everything is hard, but fair. The control is quite good too - makes you really feel that you are in charge of what your character is doing and it can be made to work just fine with keyboard and mouse after some rebinding.\nI would easlily give this game 8/10 and disregard the amount of negative feedback - most of it comes from fans of previous Dungeon Sieges, who dislike the fact that this one is nothing like them. And if you decide to add a few bux and buy a whole bundle, you can see that it's not at all a bad thing.", "hours": 53.1, "user_id": "76561198032871202", "username": "Ska-boo", "products": 59, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 49, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-01-04", "text": "Appearantly the newer games are being made for a 'wider' (dumber) audience.\nMake game not fun.. yes? Think yes.", "hours": 1.9, "username": "Diminished", "products": 275, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 49, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-01-01", "text": "This is an incredibly awful change from the previous titles. The control and moving the character is so bad on a PC that I just can't do it. If you could set the controls to mouse look that would eliminate 100% of the problem but yet again we have a titled ported to PC from console that takes advantage of NONE of the pc control mechanism. Your keyboard is a crummy dpad and your mouse has the buttons.\nIs the plot good? Is the game fun? I will never find out because the control is so bad. Something simple like turning to your left to open a chest, looting the stuff that falls on the ground and then positioning yourself back where you were is just agony.\nBeing a purely digital download there is another drawback - I can't take it out back and set it on fire for at least a little cathartic release.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561198044018954", "username": "inthrees.coprus.pete", "products": 160, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 49, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-31", "text": "I liked Dungeon Siege. I really liked Dungeon Siege 2. I wanted to like Dungeon Siege 3, but it fought me at every turn until I stopped fighting the inevitable and admitted the BEST thing that can be said about it is that it simply lacks.\nThe first two both featured adventuring with full parties. The third barely made a pretense by allowing you one companion.\nThe first two actually allowed you to create a character of your own. The third lets you pick from a very limited selection of pre-made characters, where your entire input is choosing one- you don't even get to name them.\nThe first two were both pretty linear. The third one makes the term linear seem insufficient to convey just how \"on rails\" the gameplay is.\nReplayability? Pretty close to zero, in my opinion.\nJust not seeing the appeal. At all.", "hours": 51.0, "user_id": "76561198027822566", "username": "Alois Hammer", "products": 19, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 50, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-30", "text": "There is no autosave... if you die, I hope you saved recently. I mean come on, I understand games where when you die you get pushed back a bit, or lose some gold or w/e, but no. In this game if you die your character, that means your levels your items all the abilites and talents, everything that you have done since the last time you used a save location is lost. Now there are save locations literally everywhere, but nowhere does it say that you can lose hours of play by simply not saving because your playing... thats what atosaves are for... ffs.", "hours": 5.0, "username": "Xannada", "products": 162, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 50, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-29", "text": "very pretty game. graphics are great, and the story is superbly detailed and has extreme depth. in short: it's a fun, visually appealing game", "hours": 53.1, "username": "[Horrible]Turok", "products": 81, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 50, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-27", "text": "I will never upvote or recommend a game that doesn't allow you to save.\nMy first play through I didn't have a lot of time so I messed around trying to learn which character I wanted to play then after spawning in, I quit out to go run some errands. The game's firs check point doesn't even occur after you choose a character and spawn in.\nA little further down this path there is the estate you are traveling to. A save checkpoint ok not too bad I guess. Ten minutes later after entering the estate and having my first encounter and first \"task\" given by another I quit out to get something to eat.\nCome back to it? I'm way back at the beginning of entering the estate... lol wtf?\nI'm not a big fan of the controls. In fact they're so borked I'm not even gonna try and describe them.  Suffice to say it's not a typical HnS ARPG where you highlight somethign with the mouse and then attack it. You have to actually have the character facing it. This means you have to hold down MMB constantly in a fight.  Strafing is worthless because it's not actually strafing. Pressing left or right \"strafe\" actually faces and moves your character to the left or right. It's a right-left movement key. Not a true strafe.\nThe only game series to get third person right was the first two Batman games.\nWaste of money even at five bucks for the franchise pack. Complete waste.", "hours": 0.4, "username": "\u262fUrKungFuNoGood\u262f", "products": 359, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 50, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-27", "text": "Seriously this game i so freaking bad.. the camera is bad, the skills are bad, the co-op is bad and you should not buy it. if you liked dungeon siege 2, then do not ekspekt this to be like that.. this game sucked so hard.. sheesh.. this is not a recomendation this is a warning.\nPS. this game might be somewhat decent if you play alone.. but for the love of ketchup do not play this with you're friends.", "hours": 1.8, "user_id": "76561197997747383", "username": "Lorderu", "products": 310, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
