{"product_id": "39160", "page": 50, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-26", "text": "Would say that Square Enix tried to infuse FF elements into a Diablo setting and this is what you get. Not super great unless you get a controller as the keyboard and mouse camera controls are clunky much more limited than the last two games.", "hours": 5.9, "user_id": "76561198021051254", "username": "Commodore Cockblock", "products": 470, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 50, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-26", "text": "Horrible addition to the now three part series.\nDS1 was great with its freedom of development, varied items, and pause combat.\nDS2 expanded on those three core systems and made an even better awesome pause combat game.\nThis game (DS3) butchered the freedom of development system, destroyed the item progression, and absolutely ruined the camera controls.\nThis game was nothing but and EXTREME LET DOWN following in the footsteps of DS2.\nI don't know how anyone could vote this positive having played either 1 or 2, or even neither. The game is just missing so many basic core fundamentals that are necessary for something this expensive and polished by a big name.\nIf ever there is a DS4, I pray that it is made by an entirely different team.", "hours": 5.7, "username": "Malkere", "products": 107, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 50, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-24", "text": "This isn't like the old Dungeon Siege games, they've gone for an action RPG this time.\nI wasn't sure at first but after getting hold of the controls I really liked it. Don't get me wrong, the game isn't perfect but the combat is smooth and quite challenging. The boss fights so far have been hard but not unfair and quite diverse. I might have wanted a few more skills and spells to choose from but the story and combat is enough for me to forget about that and enjoy the game.\nNot game of the year but worth the money and your time.", "hours": 14.8, "username": "Derpy Squid", "products": 725, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 50, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-23", "text": "Dungeon Siege 3 is actually a GOOD game, and you\u00b4ll enjoy it quite enough once you get past the 2 biggest problems of this game:\n1) despite the fact that it is called DUNGEON SIEGE 3, and takes place in the same fantasy world of the previous 2 DS games, other than that it HAS ABSOLUTELY NOTHING TO DO with DS1 and DS2, and if the producers of the game had not named it DS3 this game would have more appeal and approval, overall.\nLet\u00b4s see: unlike the other 2 DS, this is NOT a HACK\u00b4N\u00b4SLASH RPG, it\u00b4s a (quite good, actually) ACTION RPG, with very pretty graphics (even now, considering its age), good acting voices, a deep and intriguing storyline full of lore.\n2) A good controller is MANDATORY for this game become playable (and fun). Once you get the hang of it you\u00b4ll discover a whole different game than the one described by most of the reviews.\nSo, my advice, coming form a HUGE Dungeon Siege fan, that spent hundreds of hours on the previous titles, is to give this game a chance, making an effort to completely forget this is called Dungeon Siege 3, and after the initial hate ends, you\u00b4ll be surprised.\n8/10 (Y)", "hours": 9.5, "user_id": "76561197960976709", "username": "H\u00e4ns", "products": 201, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 50, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-21", "text": "EVen 10 minutes is enough to see what a disapointment this game is compared to the first two.  The graphics are bland, the controls are appalling and the interface is dreadful.  Dungeon Siege 2 is superior in every way.", "hours": 0.2, "user_id": "76561198089140651", "username": "joseph.bass", "products": 314, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 51, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-18", "text": "When i got this game, I thought \"Cool! Finally they made a Dungeos Siege 3 and it will be good like the first 2 and support multiplayer so I can play with my bro!\"\nOh how I was wrong...\nWhat happened to the multiplayer? it exists, but you have to look throught the same camera and you cant go out of it, you share inventory, and splitting up is impossible.\nNot that splitting up would help much anyway, they turned this game into a spam-click fight game were you occasionally buy weapons and armour and the game requires no thought at all. I played the first 2 games with my dad and my brother, but they screwed this one over, buy it in a package with the first 2 and maybe check it out if you like games were you mindlessly swing a sword or shoot a gun but other than that, I do not suggest this game 2/10.", "hours": 4.5, "username": "My Name is Amazing", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 51, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-12", "text": "Wow. I have been a big DS fan, I still own 1 and 2 the games in there cd covers and cases, but this....this is just so wrong. The controlls are wonky as all hell. Theres no chacter creation. I mean 1 and 2 it wasnt the best but you still made your chacter and played your made chacter. I liked how DS 1 and 2 did there classless progression, but this. This has premade\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665with classess. I just cant get over how bad the controls are. And yes you see that right I havent even played the game 5 mins. Its that bad. Maybe it gets better but I have no care to see it do that. So for now im giving it a 0/10", "hours": 0.7, "username": "Cyber_Wasteland", "products": 230, "early_access": false}
