{"product_id": "39160", "page": 59, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-17", "text": "this game isent bad nor good, it has an ok story... i still perfer Dungeon Siege 2's story more.\nPros:\n+Good Graphics\n+somewhat of a good story\n+Online Play\n+good selection of video options\nCons:\n-clunky Controles - Feels more like a console game\n-only 4 playable characters\n-no character customization what so ever\n-game is to easy even on hard", "hours": 19.7, "username": "Shadow", "products": 175, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 59, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-07-13", "text": "This is a great game the physics and mechanics of this game is up to scratch, but one problem, its too dam easy! But if i put it on Hardcore its too dam hard, its not so bad at the end of the game but when you start of with junk weps and its on hardcore its almost impossible to run solo and too time consuming running around dodging mobs to regerate life, However Online CO-OP Hardcore is recommended. Also it took me 5 days of playing a few hours a day to finish, and 3 days once i knew what i was doing on another character. 5/5 for graphics but the game itself 1/5, I would never recommend this RPG to anyone unless it was free. Otherwise waste of money.. IMO anyway, maybe you will like it.", "hours": 64.1, "user_id": "76561198141398677", "username": "xxmadplayerxx", "products": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 59, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-12", "text": "From what I've seen, this game is considered terrible, to which I highly disagree. This game definitely doesn't pass as a Dungeon Siege game, the only thing that qualifies it is the lore that's in it (Which I think I gathered all but one piece of). It has many nerd-service moments, in which it refers back to the original game, and even some moments that refer to the second, but it's style is entirely different. I look at games for what they are, not what they should be. It's still a good game, full of great story-telling, and an alright Combat system. The Combat System could use a bit of work, and I would have liked some more companion interraction, but it was a different developer from the first two games, so first of all, you can't expect them to go all out like they would have. Second, people need to stop saying \"It's not the same! It fails my professional inspection!\" It was a bold move to go from a, well, I don't know what genre it is, but mostly mouse controlled, to a game that actually requires some thought into combat. The combat system is very situational, and quite challenging, I can say that in the last two games, the combat mostly depended on luck, and how geared out your characters were. This one depends on actual skill, with the gear of your characters... The learning curb is a bit off, seeing as how it went from disappointing cake-walk to frustrating fires of hell, but once you figure it out, it tends to be a rather well-thought-out system that actually levels up quite nice now that I think of it.\nFor those that couldn't pay attention to my horrible rant: It's not a Dungeon Siege game, though it has the lore of it. It's still a good game, for what it is. I highly recommend it. (Unless you're stuck on nostalgia rather than gameplay)", "hours": 29.5, "user_id": "76561198042587120", "username": "Lavawalker", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 59, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-07-11", "text": "one of the worst games ive ever played.....is nothing like dungeon siege 1 and 2 which are absolute classics.\nDO NOT BUY...does not deserve to have the dungeon siege name.", "hours": 3.0, "username": "SLuRRY", "products": 434, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 59, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-07-08", "text": "Meh...it's average/slightly below for a generic hack and slash, which is part of the problem. DS 1&2 were damn good, and then you get this ____________.   You could build your character how you wanted based on spells found and weapons used, now you are stuck in predefined roles as named characters. You used to have a fairly open world to explore, now it's pretty much a guided tour...seems like things keep getting \"simplified\" for \"our benefit\" in many modern games.\nIf you can get it cheap, go ahead...It's decent, but I wouldn't suggest paying full or even half price.", "hours": 4.3, "username": "Nochty", "products": 100, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 59, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-05", "text": "I can recommend this game only if you are a fan of the Dungeon Siege saga.\nSolid aRPG which should be only played on higher difficulty levels. Game mechanics favor ranged attacks making some characters significantly stronger.", "hours": 129.8, "user_id": "76561198128360458", "username": "Mksaron", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 59, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-03", "text": "It's more like diablo than an MMO", "hours": 2.0, "user_id": "76561197976180566", "username": "GizmoMechanic", "products": 303, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 60, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-07-01", "text": "I bought the Dungeon Siege series on the summer sale for arouned \u00a36 as I had lost discs for the first game and it was worth it for the price to play again.\nI had played the beta and couldn\u00b4t really remember much of it, so I thought I\u00b4d take the leap and buy it.  The running alone killed it for me...\nEnd note, if you enjoyed the first two games, don\u00b4t let that sway you into buying this.  This has gone horribly wrong, I can\u00b4t comment of the story because I couldn\u00b4t even force myself to get far enough in.  Terrible game!", "hours": 0.5, "username": "AnnA", "products": 85, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 60, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-30", "text": "waste of money..the first two Dungeon siege was better than the dungeon siege a crapy game...", "hours": 10.1, "user_id": "76561197976403180", "username": "Dr. LosT GuY D.C.", "products": 274, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 60, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-30", "text": "Great graphics, specially with all the bells and whistles on. The camera though is awful to control and sometimes it may go to the worst angle possible within a fight.\nA good story to guide you through the game, but nothing memorable as other RPGs out there. Good voice acting though. Dragon Age: Origins set a bar for game beginnings, and I think each lead character should have a different start. I'll have to go a second playthrough to see if there's any significant differences between each one.\nThe gameplay needs some getting used to, specially if you go with mouse and keyboard, but it is fun to unleash your powers on mobs of monsters.\nOverall it is a good game. 7.5/10", "hours": 21.8, "username": "]R[ bernardofd", "products": 382, "early_access": false}
