{"product_id": "39160", "page": 61, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-24", "text": "I've played the demos of DS1 and DS2 I loved them both very much! I can't say the same for this because it has become too much like a PS3 game. There is a reason I play comupter games and not PS games! However the game was not a complete disapointment, so I think you should at least give it a try before you disregard it completely!", "hours": 34.4, "user_id": "76561198050087182", "username": "ALLAHUAKBAR!", "products": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 61, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-23", "text": "This game wasn't what I expected to buy, however that doesn't make it a \"horrible\" game, I would still recommend it. If you ever played Legion: Legend of the Excalibur, Baldurs Gate and more on the PS2, as well as Diablo, this game is reminiscent of those gameplay styles but in it's own, more simplified fashion. Combat is simple and straightforward, is fun and can keep you entertained throughout most of the game. It does tend to get a little repetitive at times, but swapping allies and changing equipment builds can help ease that. The part that's probably lacking the most is the story, which is the main focus of the game. The story isn't very original, the \"cutscenes\" are all flash animated paintings or drawings, hardly ever if at all do you get a close-up of the characters, giving an absence of connection with the story and characters in my opinion. However, I'm sure you'll be happy killing skeletons, zombies, etc. etc. regardless. It's good to catch on sale, don't pay full price for this game though, it's not worth it.", "hours": 20.5, "username": "Gaffgarion92", "products": 289, "early_access": false}
