{"product_id": "39160", "page": 69, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-27", "text": "Too linear, not enough customisation for characters.\nYou only get to use the one you start with and swap out another.\nUnimaginative boss fights.\nPredictable storyline.", "hours": 16.8, "username": "Lord THEN", "products": 633, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 69, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-26", "text": "One of the biggest let downs ive ever had. I loved the first 2 DS games, and this came free with my old graphics card, a 550 ti. it looks decent enough, but plays boringly and has voice acting that grates on the nerves due to over accentuation. if you got the game for free, then no biggy. but paying for this load is a huge rip off.", "hours": 14.5, "username": "[KINGS] The King", "products": 232, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 69, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-23", "text": "Terrible controls, camera is terrible, meh....", "hours": 0.9, "username": "Donga", "products": 286, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 69, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-23", "text": "I was a little torn on whether to give this a recommendation or not, but decided not to in the end. While I did play the entire game all the way through, I wasn't too interested in playing beyond the ending. There's a few characters to choose from, but I found that one playthrough was enough.\nIt's your quest-based RPG. You go into a zone/dungeon, you fight monsters, you fight bosses, you complete quests.\nThe gameplay was at times frustrating and not at all something that could keep me engaged.\nYou might be able to get about 20 hours from this game, but probably not a whole lot more. If you're truly interested in checking this game out, get it during a sale.", "hours": 22.5, "username": "caustically", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 69, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-23", "text": "I never played 1/2 and did not feel lost in this game.  The combat was fun and the RPG elements were flushed out fully.  The story was above average for an RPG.  The game is not a complete button masher, but it does have some button masher tendencies.  I think the combat did a good job of walking that fine line of spanning skills and still having some unique fights and play style differences.\nYou might like this game if:\nYou enjoy depth in RPGs and live action combat.", "hours": 24.9, "user_id": "76561197980786340", "username": "czman811", "products": 363, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 69, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-23", "text": "\uadf8\ub0e5\uc800\ub0e5\ud55c \uac8c\uc784", "hours": 46.8, "user_id": "76561198011044257", "username": "\u30cf\u30fc\u30c8\u30d6\u30ec\u30fc\u30af! \u304a\u5b22\u69d8", "products": 289, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 69, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-21", "text": "Worst. Sequel. Ever.\nComplete game mechanics change, stupid tree skill system... I got excited seeing it was developed with Square Enix, but was so disappointed. Not really a sequal so much as a completely new game that plays off the franchise name.", "hours": 1.9, "username": "WMcA.amenoire", "products": 416, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 69, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-20", "text": "Terrible console game. Just awful.", "hours": 21.9, "user_id": "76561197980569989", "username": "Cutter", "products": 249, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 69, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-20", "text": "A lot of people were dissapointed in this game because it was so different from the original 2.   It was definately made for Consoles more than for PC.   I found myself enjoying the game enough to give it a play through and if you have the RIG to play it in 3d you wont be dissapointed.\nDon't expect it to be anything like the first 2.  Take it for what it is and you will enjoy it.", "hours": 32.6, "user_id": "76561197970364785", "username": "Anguish", "products": 158, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 69, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-19", "text": "It's very different compared to the previous Dungeon Siege games but still a good RPG. Interesting plot, fluid combat system and meaningful decision making makes it worth playing.", "hours": 26.1, "user_id": "76561197975041945", "username": "Delfrod", "products": 843, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 70, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-18", "text": "It's like Skyrim with even more dungeons.", "hours": 5.4, "username": "Scoat the Goat", "products": 197, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 70, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-16", "text": "I have to say this is the few RPG game that I finished, Which include Van Helsing and both Torchlight. Have to say one of the best RPG experience I ever play, If you're a fan of DS I or II don't even bother with the storyline, just go with the flow and enjoy the gameplay if you're into ARPG.\nBut the game also have a flaw to be honest, I Rage and QQ while battling Jayne over her Overpowered move and teleportation, she is even harder and much more irritating than the final boss, This has to be the poor build boss to be honest, just a poor disappointment.\nBut if I want to recommend this game? I would say yes, But the score that I willing to give is 7.5/10", "hours": 14.4, "username": "Heist Cube", "products": 429, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 70, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-15", "text": "This game is one i thoroughly enjoyed. However, i am a fan of the genre of dungeon crawler. If you are not then you need not buy this game. It follows the path of every Dungeon game that has come before it. For those that are you find a very well polished experience. The graphics are sharp, the gameplay is standard, and the story intriguing. My only complaint would be the somewhat unbalanced form the 4 players you choose from have. The knight and the ranger are your best choice, and your only choice is you play alone. If you desire to play the other 2 characters. Then you need to be in a party as they are more geared toward helping, or assist party members than stand alone ones. Although this game is aimed toward multi play it shouldnt be neccasary. Complaint aside i enjoyed my time, and look foward to completeing this game again. Although i might enjoy it more with another to play with.", "hours": 1.8, "username": "J.G. Anicade", "products": 56, "early_access": false}
