{"product_id": "39160", "page": 70, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-09", "text": "WELL IF I COULD FIND A FRIEND TO PLAY WITH AND NOT FINISH AT THE FIRST LIKE 15 MINUETS MAYBE I WOULD WRITE A GOOD REVIEW BUT WHO THE \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 KNOWS MAN>\nGAME DOSNT BLOW THO", "hours": 14.9, "user_id": "76561197962480300", "username": "xdbs-traininginmountain", "products": 382, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 70, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-09", "text": "This game takes on a slightly different format than the first two in the series. I would almost call it a Diablo III clone (with lower production values), which is disappointing. If it had stayed true to the style of the series I probably would have enjoyed it a lot more. The first two games required strategy in combat and micro-managing a party of 4. DS3 combat is simplified and you only control the one character, so it gets boring pretty fast.", "hours": 26.3, "username": "PlayaSlayah", "products": 171, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 70, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-06", "text": "This game was a huge let-down. :( I ADORED DS2... and this game removed everything I loved about it. Awkward controls just sealed the coffin lid for me. So sad...", "hours": 12.0, "user_id": "76561198031296561", "username": "Lassittor", "products": 11, "early_access": false}
