{"product_id": "39160", "page": 71, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-03", "text": "Dungeon Siege III takes an interesting and well defined world and shoves it into a blender. The resulting mess is then poured down your throat like the worst karmic payback in the history of mankind. I'm only still playing it because I can't get a refund and I want as close to my money's worth as I can get.\nI mean this with all honesty when I say that DSIII has ensured that I'll never buy another game in the franchise again. Square Enix should be ashamed of themselves for utterly ruining a wonderful product line and setting with the worst control interface ever designed by human beings.\nAs a matter of fact, I highly doubt the interface was designed by men. I believe that it was, in fact, cribbed from apes.\nIf you have kids, use this foul abomination of a game as punishment. An hour attempting to accomplish anything while the controls actively conspire against you will get your children acting right. Another hour attempting to fight grotesquely overpowered bosses will ensure that they continue to act right.\nThis game gets four stars because that's how many it takes to censor the word I feel most aptly describes it.", "hours": 19.6, "username": "[IVM]Hellbilly", "products": 141, "found_funny": 6, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 71, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-02", "text": "Im not kidding when I say they litteraly threw this disk at me. Not even a joke. Even the people who made it dont want this mess.", "hours": 0.9, "username": "XenoBurger", "products": 1114, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 71, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-31", "text": "A fun action RPG. Mindless action for those times you dont want to sit down and play a involved game. The game has changed since the first Dungeon Siege which I think is still the best.", "hours": 8.5, "user_id": "76561197964796676", "username": "Viper90xt", "products": 203, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 71, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-31", "text": "Disclaimers: this is not a flawless game.  The biggest issue is that it's sometimes prone to targeting the wrong enemy. And I could have done with less cheesecake in the character designs. Finally, if you're a die hard action-rpger, you'll probably find it too short and the character abilities not diverse enough.\nThat said, I liked it.  It's certainly my favorite of the Dungeon Siege games, overall: the combat was more diverse and interesting than in 1 or 2 (though 2 had better boss fights), and the characters were given more depth.  Though certainly not the deepest tale, the story was also stronger than in the other games.  Most importantly, DS3 has a satisfying ending, with plenty of 'what happened to ...' information about the post-game world.  I leave the game feeling pretty happy about the experience, unlike DS2 and the terrible non-ending it offered up.", "hours": 15.4, "username": "crowroadaw", "products": 649, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 71, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-28", "text": "I can't say anything bad about games made by Obsidian. No exception for this game here.\nStory is deep and touching, art is beautiful, decisions you make affect the game ending, what can I say?\nThis is a really good RPG, highly recommend.", "hours": 31.6, "username": "Kaen Harel", "products": 161, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 71, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-24", "text": "Good game, decent story line, campaign could be longer and wish it had the option to actually spend my 500k gold at the end. All in all it was a fun 2 days I had in completing it.", "hours": 26.5, "username": "MonkeyDo", "products": 260, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 71, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-22", "text": "I was a huge fan of Dungeon Siege series and unfortunately this game nothing to do with DS. I played this game one hour and I was so mad that I uninstalled and shelved the game. The stupid Obsidian perk system (yeah, the same one they put in every game like they can't do anything else)  replaced the unique attribute system. The character based weapons replaced the free customization of your character. The game world is just a one straight path with locked doors. Obsidian Entertainment is a one big joke in game business and it's famous for ruining big game francishes because they doesn't respect the legendary games. Go ahead and spend your money but don't say I didn't warn you.", "hours": 1.1, "user_id": "76561198032268905", "username": "iceblood79", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
