{"product_id": "39160", "page": 72, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-15", "text": "Yet ANOTHER Diablo cloner ..... we have seen this all before .... a top down rpg hack-n-slasher kill the baddies get the loot .... **YAWN** ..... was bored quickly on this one. Diablo did it much better. If you have played Diablo or any of its clones (Torchlight, Dungeon Siege< Torchlight 2 etc) then you have played this one. Nothing new or innovating here just another cash cloner.", "hours": 1.0, "user_id": "76561198034340520", "username": "Muerkier", "products": 202, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 72, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-14", "text": "I tried it a second time b/c I couldn't remember why I stopped.  Took me 5 minute of playing to remember.  I really really enjoyed the first one, kind of enjoyed the second one, and well, this one continued the downward trend.  Very dissapointing graphics, slim to no depth of strategy, confusing and forgettable storyline (a killer for RPGs).  Go buy the first one instead, you'll get a good 50-100hrs out of it.", "hours": 12.7, "username": "Wakko", "products": 72, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 72, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-14", "text": "I like to use the Terminator series to explain the Dungeon Siege series.\nDS1 -> A classic, has issues, (even more so now with modern OS's)\nDS2 -> a great sequel, probably the greatest sequel ever.\nDS3 -> Hard to live up to its previous greatness.\nBut in all seriousness, Its pretty, it plays alright, the boss at the end is a bit of a buggy dissapointment. Its just not as good as 2. Youre probably gonna buy this with the other 2 in the series, and they are all worth your time.", "hours": 27.8, "user_id": "76561198031750715", "username": "Zoah", "products": 363, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 72, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-11", "text": "This game is nothing like the 1rst or 2nd. They completly went a different direction and killed the series. Shared screen multiplayer...seriously we went back to the nintendo? The controls are terrible if you want to use a keyboard and a mouse which a lot of people on a computer want to do...imagine that. It looks pretty...other then that it sucks.", "hours": 9.7, "user_id": "76561197982058344", "username": "Tiaka", "products": 132, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 72, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-10", "text": "Good game but I got stuck.  I hate when I get stuck.", "hours": 9.0, "user_id": "76561197965417542", "username": "Gary", "products": 142, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 72, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-08", "text": "I bought this and the expansion for about three bucks during the christmas sale and expected to just kind of\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665around with it for a few hours until I got tired of it. I was surprised that I was drawn in as much as I was, however, and certainly not for the reason I expected. The combat is honestly pretty boring and tedious especially later on. The boss battles in particular can be a slog (the final boss of the DLC in particular is just awful). The loot is boring, there is no exploration to speak of and the skills (at least for the class I played) were nothing special. So why would I still recommend this game? I was actually drawn in by the story. This is something that VERY rarely happens to me with video games but there is something about the setting and the interactive dialogue choices that really clicked with me here. Would I recommend this to just anyone? No, probably not, but for anyone who wants a pretty mindless action rpg with a story that blows most diablo-likes out of the water (and coop), I would say go for it. I actually plan on playing it again in a year or two, probably.", "hours": 23.2, "username": "Beeves", "products": 2432, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 72, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-07", "text": "This game is horrible I am a big fan of the loot fest and dugeon crawler genre this does not hold up to dungeon siege 1 or 2 it is that bad. do not by this game out of curiosty you will regret spending 15 dollars. 3/10", "hours": 1.3, "username": "Migrating", "products": 99, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 72, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-07", "text": "I haven't actually played the first two games but from what I've heard they were awesome. DS III is abit different from what I've played before but I like it nonetheless, the story is interesting and it wasn't at all hard to get used to the whole idea of the gameplay. I won't say that it is one of my favourite games of all times because... well it isn't :P it does keep you entertained though so if you have nothing else to do give it a try :D:", "hours": 40.3, "user_id": "76561198104139996", "username": "\u2735 Contessa \u2735", "products": 63, "early_access": false}
