{"product_id": "39160", "page": 72, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-06", "text": "The first game from Obsidian I have to give the down finger. It's a shait console port, and even worse, it completely did away with the character system and playstyle from Dungeon Siege I and II. Some good characters and playing co-op are the only redeeming qualities, so if a) you are not a fan of the first two games and b) can withstand consolitis, you may want to try it for the aforementioned redeeming qualities.", "hours": 14.3, "username": "Tychoxi", "products": 996, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
