{"product_id": "39160", "page": 73, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-01", "text": "I got bored with this rather quick. I loved the original Dungeon Siege game but I felt like I was doing more running around than anything else with this release. In addition, I found the game's POV annoying in a lot of movement and combat situations. If you like RPGs I'd recommend looking elsewhere from something a bit more enjoyable to play.", "hours": 4.6, "username": "Xyriin", "products": 127, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 73, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-01", "text": "Playing this game with the male mage makes this game a joy to play.   After playing this game with a female half red spawn and having a the blues.  Replaying with another character made this game a breeze and a blast.  Even though this game doesn't reminde me of dungeon siege it is still a lot of fun and worth your time if you like single player action rpg.  The whole game can be taking out with DLC in about 10 hours if your dying all over the place.  Give it a chance", "hours": 46.5, "user_id": "76561197991083339", "username": "louterrence1", "products": 345, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 74, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-30", "text": "its pretty good", "hours": 3.2, "user_id": "76561198093718152", "username": "tAoE_Cub", "products": 109, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 74, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-30", "text": "Yes I think it is easily on my top ten Steam games because of how fun it is and the story is amazing!", "hours": 9.3, "username": "Nix", "products": 40, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 74, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-30", "text": "What happened to this franchise?  The first and second games were incredible, this one is a like somebody decided to release a technology demo as a full-fledged game.\nIt's the best looking Dungeon Siege game yet but that's where the praise ends.  I tried to like it but was thwarted at every turn.\nA weird game save system, frequently finding yourself woefully overmatched, a weak storyline and of course those awful camera angles that have you looking at walls instead of your opponent.  Control is vague at best which combined with the goofy camera angles make the game tedious to play.  You spend more time compensating for the interface than worrying about your quests.  That's a shame because the maps are gorgeous and painstakingly rendered but the technical problems with the game ruin the immersion.\nIt took the \"Play\" out of Role Playing Game...\nI actually bought a copy of Dungeon Siege 3 for a friend of mine who's an avid RPG player which included previous Dungoen Siege games.  I was hoping for the same hundreds of co-op gameplay hours we enjoyed with Dungeon Siege 2.\nHe loaded it up, played it for 30 minutes and said to me, \" I can't play this...\"\nThere's not much more to say...", "hours": 5.9, "username": "dudz_fryd", "products": 99, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
