{"product_id": "39160", "page": 74, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-28", "text": "This game is not fun - camera controls are terrible, especially when playing co-op, it basically ruins everything, very hard battles even on easy difficulty. I'm not against hard games, but sometimes DS III is stupidly hard, without any reason. It's not a hack-and-slash, it's not a classic RPG... it's very hard to enjoy.\nI realy hoped it will be great, but i'm dissapointed.", "hours": 2.1, "username": "Morgen", "products": 499, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 74, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-26", "text": "Another prime example of the dangers of consolification: take a gear grinder with a hundred available skills to give near-infinite character customization, and shoehorn it into a system where the player is only expected to bind five or six buttons and then mash them like a retard.\nThis game killed the license.", "hours": 2.2, "username": "PuppetSoul", "products": 132, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 74, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-24", "text": "If you grew up playing Dungeon Seige 1 and 2 then you will be slightly dissapointed, but I highly recomend playing if you are into this genre, It's not what it could have been but it was still a fun game. A little short but very interesting", "hours": 8.9, "username": "Trip_Fox", "products": 189, "early_access": false}
