{"product_id": "39160", "page": 75, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "Dungeon Siege III is an action R.P.G. developed by Obsidian Entertainment and published by Square Enix. For centuries Legionnaires have protected the nation of Ehb until they were betrayed and all but driven to the brink of extinction. Years later, now that evil has returned to Ehb the people turn to the few remaining Legionnaires for the protection of the past. As an heir to the Legion will you accept this plea for help? Dungeon Siege III is the latest entry in the beloved long running classic roleplaying series from Square Enix. It is worth nothing though that this title is quite different from the previous games in the series.\nAt the start of the game you choose one of four different character classes and set off on an adventure to take back the nation of Ehb from an evil force that has gained control of the land and declared war on all of the former protectors of Ehb known as Legionnairies. Dungeon Siege III has all the elements of a traditional roleplaying game with you, the player, gaining experience points through combat, various tasks, completing quests and discovering lore. You can use these points to upgrade your chosen characters abilities to your particular style of play through a fairly diversified skill tree. There is also a great amount of loot to be collected in the form of weapons, armor and trinkets that can be accquired through combat, exploration and different merchants scattered throughout the land. Choosing the right weapons and items for your character as well as for your companion are vital to your survival as the narrative plays out. Even though the plot in this game is a story that has been portrayed many times before, I was really entertained with the way it was presented in Dungeon Siege III and thoroughly enjoyed the adventure from start to finish.\nGraphically I think this game is beautiful, it's played in a isometric top-down view much like \"Diablo\" and the \"Baldur's Gate\" titles. From the dense Rukkenvahl Forest, through the beautifully cobbled streets of Stonebridge to the mines of Glitterdelve and beyond, the environments of Ehb are varied and full of the little details that one looks for in games of this type. The title also uses a gorgeous color palette and blends in depth of field effects quite nicely both during gameplay and cutscene dialog. The sound quality is exceptional whether it's the sound of combat, dialog or just ambient background noises as you travel across the land. Also of note is the terrific musical score which is quite memorable in this game. There are a couple of tracks that I would really like to own but sadly the soundtrack to this title is not available anywhere and believe me I checked. To summarize, I really like R.P.G.'s that take you on a quest to a wide variety of locations and Dungeon Siege III excels at this while providing quite a visual feast for the eyes.\nI really enjoyed my first playthrough of Dungeon Siege III despite some problems with the camera angles at times during combat. The story was intriguing, the combat was alot of fun, the characters and lore was quite interesting as well. Each of the four available characters have vastly different styles of combat so the replayability of this title is high. I plan to go back and play again with each of the other characters at some point. Though I have to admit that for some strange reason I remember downloading and playing the demo of this game right before it launched a few years ago and I did not like it. I can only believe that is because of my gaming habits having changed around that time and me moving more towards R.P.G.'s like \"The Elder Scrolls\" and \"Kingdoms Of Amalur\" and away from the old-school roleplaying games that first captured my interest in the genre to begin with. I don't know...all I can say now is that this is indeed a great game despite all the HATE that it constantly receives and is RECOMMENDED for roleplaying gamers.", "hours": 67.5, "username": "\u03c1\u043e\u0455\u03b9\u0442\u044f\u043e\u0438_", "products": 470, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 75, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "VERY dissapointed by this game ... imo the only bad game i bought ever :(\nafter the great Dungeon Siege 1 and good Dungeon Siege 2 ... they made a good looking shiny , short , ultra linear , boring game", "hours": 66.2, "user_id": "76561198044848921", "username": "Sims", "products": 75, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 75, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "Decent Diablo 3 clone.", "hours": 9.9, "user_id": "76561197962800267", "username": "Tactical Tez", "products": 29, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 75, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-20", "text": "this games horrible only in comparrison to the games that it is exactly like and came out around the same time as it, play torchlight or diablo instead.", "hours": 2.8, "username": "Dark Instinct", "products": 203, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 75, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-19", "text": "Really fun game, wish you could have different pov's and didnt have to stay near your party all the time.", "hours": 8.7, "user_id": "76561198018735394", "username": "NoFearJoker", "products": 205, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 75, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-18", "text": "Nice game but co-op multiplayer just suck, 2 players have to be on screen all the time which is frustrating as hell, however its nice singeplayer slasher :)", "hours": 10.0, "username": "frankcastle51", "products": 4125, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 75, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-18", "text": "Bad game....literally bought it on day one expecting good things as i liked the others....the loot system here is so BROKEN, literally picked up an item within the first item that was THE BEST item in the game.....loot doesn't scale with you, and it's all the same\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 over and over and over....and then lets talk about the mobs, literally just backflip and shooting off screen all day because of severe bad balancing....bosses are a joke, small mobs are harder then these things.....graphics are okay but I don't rally care if everything looks cool, I like to have fun playing a game...oh yea, the save game feature IS GARBAGE...omfg it is a joke...", "hours": 3.4, "user_id": "76561198024273535", "username": "illidian", "products": 112, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 75, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-16", "text": "Utter and absolute\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\nIf you liked DS1 and DS2, this contains very few of the elements that game did.\nThis is another Square Enix project grandfathered from Gas Powered Games (for example, they have the Supreme Commander franchise, and when they made a sequel to that, it in no way matched up with its prequel). As usual, they trashed it and left us with something that makes you feel physically ill to play.", "hours": 0.6, "user_id": "76561197994897424", "username": "The Church of Flarisu", "products": 160, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 76, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-14", "text": "If you liked Dungeon Siege 2, leave now because this is not the same. Biggest disappointment ever... How do you screw up an awesome game?", "hours": 3.1, "username": "Chris", "products": 641, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 76, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-12", "text": "You need to play this one alone or with three other people and have yourself a controller to fully enjoy the game.\nIt's horrendous to try to play Multiplayer as 2 or 3 people, and incredibly confusing for whatever reason until you hit all four.\nThat aside, it's still a very fun, simple yet challenging dungeon crawler with a decent story.\nDon't pick this game up and expect it to be anything like the original 2 Dungeon Siege games! Play style is no longer the above dungeon crawler but instead a third-person crawler with a lot less customization. Each character has their own set of skills that can't be changed.", "hours": 43.0, "username": "\u039e\u044f\u044fo\u044f \u0298n\u0298", "products": 46, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 76, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-11", "text": "If you're used to the theme and style of DS1 and 2 then this one might shock the senses a bit.  It has the Square Enix flavor all over it, which might be good in some of the games they tend to churn out, but I definitely don't want it in my Dungeon Siege.  The game is just unbearable to me, I loved the original Dungeon Siege despite it being incredibly simple, everything just seemed to fit into place.   DS III you can just stay far away, I'll go back to being a \"humble farmer\".", "hours": 0.2, "username": "Gava", "products": 481, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 76, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-10", "text": "Hello,\nDungeon Siege 2 always gave me a Diablo 2 with a better story vibe. Dungeon Siege 3, while coming out before Diablo 3, plays very much like it. Quality between the third installments of the two series are much the same. If you like one, you will like the other. I don't much care for either of them (though the second installments of each were very fun).\nI do not recommend this game. Go play Dungeon Siege 2 instead. Much better game (I think).\nCheers,\nMichael", "hours": 7.0, "user_id": "76561198047237535", "username": "[ICG] Vagabond", "products": 272, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 76, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-08", "text": "This game effectively killed the series - after falling in love with dungeon siege and it's expansions and sequel I have no clue who directed the game into this pile of\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 Absolute trash GUI, mechanics, clunky AI, terrible skills, nothing that was loved about 1 or 2 is here.", "hours": 4.8, "username": "Shalandir", "products": 624, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 76, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-08", "text": "I loved Dungeon Siege II and when my friend asked me if I wanted this I freaked out, it has a nice story and fun gameplay", "hours": 22.6, "username": "Auske (Goodbye forever friends)", "products": 112, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 76, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-07", "text": "Much different in scheme and layout than the other previous Dungeon Siege games, and the default video settings will kill your computer if you're not running some high-powered machine. Although you can select what character to play as, it lacks the character customization features of the previous titles.", "hours": 1.0, "user_id": "76561198043899784", "username": "Il Duce-bag", "products": 33, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 76, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-04", "text": "Horribly underrated game. The controls are a bit strange, but once you get past the initial learning curve, it's incredibly fun. Beautiful graphics even on a lower end system, visceral combat, interesting characters/classes. The story's also a lot better than you'd expect, though it may not seem that way at first. Gameplay's a bit of a departure from the previous installments in the series (to say the least), but most changes are for the better, and the story connects back to the first game's much better than DS2's did.\nMy only major complaints are that the audio can be buggy at times, and some of the voice acting is what I will politely call less than stellar. But even with those issues, it's one of the best RPGs I've played in a long time.", "hours": 76.9, "user_id": "76561198045291203", "username": "ensignedwards", "products": 70, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 76, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-04", "text": "awesome game, should get it, so we can play together", "hours": 24.0, "user_id": "76561198023403343", "username": "Mags", "products": 186, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 76, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-03", "text": "Terrible control.\nHorrible narrative.\nUninspired combat mechanics.\nVoice actors are mediocre at best.\nWould not reccommend.\nThis is definietly a stepback from the greatness of what made Dungeon Siege was suppose to be.", "hours": 5.7, "username": "Hyphixsys", "products": 367, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 77, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-03", "text": "If you're getting this for co-op, don't bother.  Unless one of you likes the idea of not having his own character.", "hours": 1.1, "user_id": "76561197993794445", "username": "dark.link73337", "products": 1046, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 77, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-01", "text": "This is in my opinion a decent hack and slash title that imitates Diablo with a limited consequence system. For example, you get to make decisions such as letting someone live and that may benefit you or not later on.\nWhile I could complete the game on medium with a keyboard, a controller would have been far better as I rarely used the block function anyway.\nWhat the game has going for it is a nice colour palette, satisfying combat and a deep system to customise your character's skills and equipment rules. I also love is that there is next to no time for loading between areas and thankfully this game doesn't bother with a checkpoint system.\nWhere it falls is that the character's aren't that interesting. I played as Anjali who is a fire being of some kind. Yet her dialogue options were just dull. Now there are some funny lines from some of the characters so you will get a jolt of humour or two.\nAlso the AI of your partner can be annoying at times as you have no control over it. When your character gets knocked out, your partner can you revive you. Now you'd think that your partner would make it their priority to get you back on your feet. Wrong. Some times they will but sometimes they'll just mess about, doing their thing until either they finally come over or they die. Furthermore, if there's 4 characters, why can you only have 1 partner. Surely the mission to save the world (yup, no points for plot originality) would be better served with 4 peeps rather than 2.\nFinding your objective can also be tricky, especially with multiple levels of height in areas. Then there's the inventory system which while ok could be worked better. It takes time to get all 3 other partners but you can start getting their stuff from the get go. Stuff that only 1 person can use. Carrying it seems like a waste of space so there will be a ruthless amount of selling to be done.\nOn the whole my experience with this game was positive. As mentioned above there's tons of loot, good enemy variety, interesting enemy variety and the world comes across as having depth. Eventually I will try a second character so replayability as well.\nRegards\nOn the whole though, my experience with this game was positive.", "hours": 39.7, "user_id": "76561198064303459", "username": "Dantihero", "products": 196, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 77, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-01", "text": "Third part of the game was the one I have spent most of the time. I had thought it can offer the best experience but I did not manage to check it out fully.\nWhole plot seems to be interesting but game linearity was bothering me so much that I couldn't forget I am guided by a hand not even once.\nThere is also something else which is bad: nice ascetic limited by \"one screen camera lock\" for co-op play. This had made me so annoyed that whole game became unplayable after just a few hours. And I've never looked back at it.", "hours": 4.0, "username": "Ewelinka", "products": 226, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 77, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-30", "text": "This game is different than the previous installments:\nGOOD: This game has many types of stats a player can have. Everytime the player levels up, so does enemies, so there will always be a challenge. Lots of replay value, and graphics are not bad.\nBAD: Although it has many replay value, it tends to become repetitive, making it boring after awhile.\nEITHER: If you play by yourself, your companion tends to become stupid when you die. ( Your companion would have to revive you if you die.) Although your companion is stupid, you can customize your companion to equip equipment as well, acting as if you have 2 players to control, but an AI is controlling 1 character while you control the other.\nSCORE: 7.5/10 Get this if you got friends to play with, otherwise not a good single-player game.", "hours": 27.5, "username": "\u239b\u239dGoldberg\u23a0\u239e", "products": 503, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 77, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-30", "text": "Horrible control scheme designed for an Xbox controller, terrible camera, shallow gameplay. Would be tolerable in coop except for the fact that the view is centered around the host like an old SNES game. Pure garbage, I hope this company goes out of business soon.", "hours": 34.3, "username": "Menckenstein", "products": 314, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 77, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-29", "text": "Diablo on steroids", "hours": 2.2, "user_id": "76561198010934942", "username": "Plague", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 77, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-29", "text": "The worst camera ever seen! Epic fail.", "hours": 2.6, "username": "177 zsc", "products": 51, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 77, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-27", "text": "Sucks as a single player game, but multiplayer creates its own problems.  Xbox 360 controller required.", "hours": 25.2, "username": "Merlin4", "products": 250, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 77, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-27", "text": "While not as imersive as the previous installments of Dungeon Siege this sequel is still very good. The story line is compelling and the game play while not as versatile is still a worthy mechanic. AS has been the problem with previous versions the camera system needs work but overall it doesn't make gameplay more difficult. This game while fun is also not an elitist title where you have to have a top skillset to play well. Hope you enjoy it as much as I have :)", "hours": 25.9, "user_id": "76561198055121346", "username": "madeye.mcbaine", "products": 132, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 77, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "Dungeon Siege. A game about smashing, looting, and wrecking the place, with no care or consequence for the world.\nWhen I saw this game release, my co-op buddy and I grabbed a copy and immediately jumped into the game to play. The Co-op was decent enough, though you can troll the other guy in a few irritating ways. Most horribly, however, is the fact that co-opter, the person joining the host, does not retain -anything- their character aquires when they leave the match. Instead, the hosts alternate character maintains the items. Thus, it's not so much co-op, as it is \"You're my B****\".\nIn the end, we never could make ourselves continue to play it, after discovering that, and thus, never beat it.", "hours": 11.6, "user_id": "76561197964405424", "username": "Icarius Fallen", "products": 738, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 78, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "This game has an excelent story line and beautiful character development. An excelent choice.", "hours": 25.6, "user_id": "76561197986717785", "username": "Yetiking", "products": 146, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 78, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "Not a perfect game by any means, but I really enjoyed it, especially for the price I purchased it at. It was a very pretty game graphically, and though somewhat generic at first, I actually found myself drawn in by the story. Overall, very enjoyable and rewardingly difficult.", "hours": 31.0, "user_id": "76561198019319817", "username": "The Waffle Cometh", "products": 172, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 78, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-21", "text": "For centuries legionnaires have protected the nation of Ehb until they were betrayed and all but driven to the brink of extinction. Now that evil has returned to Ehb the people turn to the few remaining Legionnaires for the protection of the past. As an heir to the legion will you accept this plea for help? How it will all be resolved is up to you!\nDungeon Siege III is an Action RPG that seamlessly blends intuitive fast-paced gameplay, a robust RPG system featuring a large selection of abilities, loot galore and the depth of story Square-Enix and Obsidian Entertainment are known for creating. Players will be able to adventure by themselves, on the couch with friends, or online in a fully multiplayer experience.", "hours": 785.7, "username": "Tuong", "products": 2374, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 78, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-16", "text": "More arcade-style action than I was expecting, this is still a pretty fun action/RPG. I don't know if the co-op is any good (the game seems to tout that as one of its main features), as I only played single-player.\nA pretty polished game overall, with enough depth to the combat to keep the otherwise-mindless slaughter of enemies interesting. The boss fights can be a little gimmicky, but that's true for damned near every hack-n-slash action game these days.", "hours": 18.3, "username": "Cactmoore", "products": 199, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 78, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-07", "text": "Dungeon Siege III is definitely a Dungeon Siege game. Like its predecessors, it blends action-RPG gameplay with the character development of a more traditional RPG. However, the gameplay in Dungeon Siege III is bland, and the combat is dull and repetitive. Maybe it gets better, but I lost interest pretty quickly. It's a sort of console-friendly Dungeon Siege.\nThe storyline seems to expect you to be playing Co-op with friends, and maybe that would add variety to the fights. But solo, it's really difficult to stay interested, when most of what you're doing is mowing down wave after wave of enemies in the same way, over and over, and you make your way from point A to point B.\nThis is an uninspired game, not worthy of your time.", "hours": 1.3, "username": "7grain", "products": 355, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 78, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-21", "text": "Dungeon Siege III offers an enjoyable story driven dungeon crawler experience with RPG elements built in to help replayability.  Shockingly there is still an active community so it is easy to find others to play co-op with.  For the price you get a ton of content and the visuals up to par with other modern AAA dungeon crawler releases.", "hours": 23.9, "username": "SinicalGeek", "products": 930, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 78, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-19", "text": "People who were fans of the first 2 games in the series love to\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665all over this game. But they should not be paid attention to. This game in and of itself is pretty great and provides a good gameplay experience so long as you're not wearing your nostalgia goggles.", "hours": 75.2, "username": "JoeyBeanz", "products": 742, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 78, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-07", "text": "Not a bad game, but no one play though.", "hours": 4.1, "username": "Tarnia_Q", "products": 2504, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 78, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-01", "text": "Great, and challenging game!", "hours": 33.1, "username": "kittycairo", "products": 299, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 78, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-26", "text": "Obsidian, I love you for your deep, detailed, thoughtful stories that take me places and make me think thoughts and\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665br>\nhack and slashers do not become you", "hours": 0.3, "username": "CarlCX", "products": 2373, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 79, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-23", "text": "As a Diablo-eque hack & slasher, Dungeon Siege III is far from the usual fare you've come to expect from Obsidian. While the game is fairly linear, where forks in the main path usually means loot chests or side missions, choices being reflected in the epilogue was a nice touch and a welcomed addition.\nInstead of building a party, you only control 1 character with 1 other character deployed as an AI companion. Combat involves mixing up the 9 skills, and their empowered variety; the stances switching and constant dodging reminded me a little of Bastion's combat.\nThe game is pretty and practically glitch-free. It is a shame that the beautiful character models were rarely showcased as the dialogue camera never panned over to your character, other than in the DLC. Other mild annoyances are the slow-ish walk speed and restrictive camera pitch.\nOne feature they did retain from the Dungeon Siege brand was the huge continuous world. It's quite amazing how the lack of loading screens can add to the enjoyment of a game.\nAll in all, I can understand why Dungeon Siege fans condemn it and others bemoan its \"console dumb-down\". Dungeon Siege III seems to suffer from the recent trend of being a decent game but also a \"bad\" entry in a franchise, however it should still be an enjoyable distraction for a budget price.\nNOTE: probably best played on a gamepad", "hours": 21.2, "username": "joe", "products": 512, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 79, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-09-23", "text": "The worst Coop game I've ever played. Obsidian what have you done???\n2/5 \u2605\u2605\u2606\u2606\u2606", "hours": 3.2, "user_id": "76561198031330490", "username": "Cstof", "products": 1288, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 79, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-09-19", "text": "This game is a lot like being constipated: it leaves you with a vague sense of accomplishment, but mostly there's just a lot of bored waiting.\nThe game bears little resemblance to DS 1 and 2, and feels more like a generic title crapped out onto the XBox Live Marketplace in the hopes of making a few bucks from people that remember the name and thought it might be worth playing. It's not.", "hours": 12.7, "username": "ShakespearOnIce", "products": 244, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 79, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-15", "text": "i highly recommend this game!\nfor best experience play with a friend and 2 controllers for the entire campaign and you wont regret it!\none more thing, get the DLC its really good and adds a lot of stuff to the game.\nyou like an action RPG games?\nyou have 2 xbox 360 controllers?\nyou like to play games locally?\nif all your answers are yes than you must buy this game.", "hours": 36.8, "user_id": "76561197999790854", "username": "The Punisher", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 79, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-12", "text": "This game has its faults, like a clunky inventory, an inefficient notification system, and also forcing you to rebind your keys before getting into the game, but somehow this game still holds enough polish to shine. The gameplay is a great, hack and slash dungeon crawler. This adventure is also a fair example of how straightforward RPGs can still tell great stories without a load of optional, distracting, inconsequential side quests that require you to go out of your way and stray far from the main storyline. The land of Ehb is a rich and colourful one that more people should take a chance to explore.", "hours": 53.0, "username": "Kovaelin", "products": 581, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 79, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-01", "text": "A nice sweet and simple game.  If you like dungeon runners, then you'll lvoe this game.   The controls are a little shaky but once you get the hang of it, it's super fun!  Especially if you're looking for a little game to just play when no one is online!\nHave fun!", "hours": 19.9, "username": "Clyde", "products": 111, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 79, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-01", "text": "Gah! You want to love this game after playing the first two but just like the other two the camera controls blow on this game. However lets not dwell on something so small as far as the story line of this game goes it is very well thought out and it really shows as you play it. I have yet to totally finish the game because I am playing with a friend and don't plan on finishing it solo until I have finished it in coop. However the bit of time I have spent on this game I really did enjoy it the game didn't feel like I was grinding my way to the end but rather enjoying a story as I progressed in the game. Which made the game even more fun to play but one thing that the game is not forgiving about is the lack of starting tutorials now while this might be due to the fact I started in coop rather than solo it left me trying to really figure out all the odd controls. Once I figured it out though I was rolling along without too much trouble. Well worth getting if the price is right for you just for the story and looks alone this game is worth it and should be considered when you buy it.", "hours": 14.0, "username": "ac19189", "products": 967, "early_access": false}
