{"product_id": "39160", "page": 80, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-12", "text": "This played like a blend of Diablo 3 and Dragon Age. It is a pretty standard RPG - build yourself up, save the world, sort of deal. The graphics are lovely, and visually pleasing, but most of the world is standard fair (but very well done). I really enjoyed the combat, except for the camera mechanics. They know how to make worthy boss fights too, and keep the difficulty at a good level. Most bosses took a few tries to get past, a few were smooth, and several took many attempts. The length of boss fights was plenty long - it felt like a BOSS fight since you'd be battling for 5-15mins, instead of blasting them down super fast. Normal mode kept me on my toes, but wasn't gruesomely painful - which is how I like normal modes. I think the weakest point is the character development, for there really isn't much. There are a few fun phrases, but nothing to make you glom onto the characters and love them as you would in Dragon Age.  7.5/10, would recommend to RPG adventure fans easily.", "hours": 29.6, "username": "Cyradis314", "products": 261, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 80, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-12", "text": "A flawed game unlike the other Dungeon Siege titles, or most other Obsidian games either. I don't know how fun I'd describe it as? It's... it's actually MASSIVELY bland. And pretty short. And one of the systems I enjoyed most was apparently only in the game because I bought the DLC, so that's another half-strike.\nI don't know whether to praise or damn this game. It's seriously some kind of limbo-state. Very controller-centric action RPG gameplay, probably one of the worst co-op setups I've seen in ages off of consoles (only the host keeps gear/save data/XP! \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 you, other guy! don't go trying to bring your character up in here!), but then it adapts some of my favorite quirks of the genre (story choices and actions in-game giving you perma-perks to stats, controllable evolutions of skills, solid amount of customization for your characters within their roles).\nIf you buy this: buy it with the Treasures of the Sun DLC. You may as well - the game's a bit short, and TotS gives you some cool new toys and a rather fun new region. Just know going in that the game is not amazing by any standards. On the other hand, it doesn't really \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 UP anywhere that I can point out, either.\nI still don't know how the hell I feel about this, and I've been debating it with myself for about a week now as I played it to completion.", "hours": 15.4, "username": "uncertified bisexual", "products": 5564, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 80, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-07", "text": "Dungeon Siege III is a great game, but it simply isn't a Dungeon Siege anymore. The gameplay mechanics are very, very simplified compared to original Dungeon Siege, or even a Dungeon Siege 2. Nevertheles, it is a great, solid, rather simplistic RPG with beautiful graphics and engaging gameplay, but do not expect almost anything you've used to in previous installments.", "hours": 1.2, "username": "nightquaker", "products": 495, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 80, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-04", "text": "Very good and interesting story line. Decent gameplay. Not a whole lot of re-play value however.", "hours": 17.8, "username": "Kedigori", "products": 141, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 80, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-07-31", "text": "This game feels awfully similar to Dragon Age II while playing it, though it is a LOT harder. The similarities to Dragon Age II also means that Dungeon Siege III doesn't play even remotely similarly to the previous two DS titles. It's an extremely good game if you can live with the high difficulty level, and because it is so different to the first two DS titles, it is not essential that you play those two games before this one.", "hours": 5.1, "username": "Lukozer", "products": 442, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 80, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-07-24", "text": "If you like RPGs and a bit of hack 'n' slash, this game is for you. Lot's of fun, good story line, good characters and super addicting. Parts can be hard (boss fights) but definitely worth it. There was a lot of thought put into this game and there are a lot of different ways your decisions affect it. Haven't beaten it (about 25% of the way through, I think) and I absolutely LOVE it. Sometimes it's hard to pull myself away, haha. Definitely a good buy and a good way to pass the time. Long Live the Legion!!\nEdit: I beat the game quite awhile ago and forgot to update the review. I was addicted to the very end and was very sad when the game finally came to a halt. I ended up having to replay the last bit cause I missed one of the achievements which kept me from getting the fully-win-the-game achievement. At some point I hope to play the other three characters, but I really liked Anjali so it might be a hard change.\nThere are quite a few interesting aspects in the game that I enjoyed. The skill selection process, for one, as well as the essences to add boosts to your character by way of weapons and armor. The multiplayer is certainly not the greatest, it would be if it didn't have a tethered camera. There is a way around this, but I am not desperate enough for a multiplayer to deal with adjusting the game by way of editing files.\nSo all in all, I would suggest buying this game to play solo. If you want it for the multiplayer aspect, I think I should say to skip it.\nEditEdit: I forgot to mention this is a linear game, meaning it follows a pretty solid track with no real free roam. I didn't find it bothersome, but some others might so I figured it should be thrown out there. :)", "hours": 35.8, "username": "Vaeaea", "products": 266, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 80, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-07-20", "text": "Although this 3rd installment of the series is not by the traditional studio that started it, they managed to keep it intact for the most part. Satsfying combat mechanics, realistic plotline, fast paced and generally fun to play. The main downside in this game is the lack of variation, the relative short playtime until completion and generally doesn't honor the epic lands as they were depicted in DS1 or 2. Overall, i'd reccomend it if you're fan of the series, but overall it felt too short and linear at times.", "hours": 32.9, "username": "Cyriel \u16ed\u16b2\u16c3\u16b1\u16c1\u16d6\u16da\u16ed", "products": 854, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 80, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-07-17", "text": "This game turned out to be an awesome game.  The story was good and the battles got much better as you gained powers.  The quick switching from one form to another made the battles interesting and fun.  If you like games like diablo and torchight then you shoulf like this game too.  Get the bundle with the original two games for 3 times the fun.  I plan on playing again to try another class.", "hours": 40.0, "user_id": "76561197982782989", "username": "Nitehawk", "products": 250, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 81, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-07-11", "text": "After Dungeon Siege and Dungeon Siege II, I was again expecting a nice action RPG. Dungeon Siege III has serious flaws. The camera has a fixed perspective, the drop items are horrible, there's only a single layout to go through, and because the items drops are terrible, item grinding is useless as there's no respawning or dungeons like in Dungeon Siege II.\nDo not buy! Rated 3 out of 10.", "hours": 48.5, "username": "bFunk", "products": 4260, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 81, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-07-10", "text": "While DS1 was a fairly boring hack and slash with a fantastic modding community, and DS2 an obvious attempt at trying to be more like Diablo 2, DS3 might as well be from a different series. That's not to say however, that it is a bad game, merely questionably named. DS3 drops most of the grinding and instead plays more like an action game. Loot and leveling still exist, but the emphasis is placed on the combat and story. The story isn't anything to write home about, but it's still significantly better than the first 2 games in the series, and most action RPGs in general. The combat is where this game shines, different weapon and skill combinations can accent any play style, and it's just flat out fun to play. The controls, especially with KBAM, may take some getting used to, but the game is worth it in the end.", "hours": 16.9, "username": "Malignant Bear", "products": 985, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 81, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-07-04", "text": "A good game with a good storyline that keeps you on your toes. And man the characters are cool.", "hours": 18.7, "user_id": "76561198067495920", "username": "Nickadonis", "products": 158, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 81, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-06-29", "text": "As a huge fan of DS2, I was extremely disappointed in the direction they took for DS3.  That said, DS3 is still a solid action RPG - it just wasn't what I was hoping for.\nI tried playing the melee dude on the highest difficulty.  Regular mobs are pretty \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing difficult, and I loved it, but some of the bosses are damn near impossible.  They have so much health and can take out 1/3 of your life in one hit. Play this on normal difficulty.", "hours": 6.0, "username": "Eincrou", "products": 305, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 81, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-06-28", "text": "Dungeon Siege 3 is, IMO, 3/5 stars. The original Dungeon Siege franchise used to be a party based, hack/slash game that focused on highly customizable character and party selections;  however, the latest installment was a blatant clone of the Diablo franchise, without the strengths that Diablo has. While it is still a strong installment, it does not live up to the expectations or any of the potential that the release had.\nThe main problem is that the game play was far easier than any prior Dungeon Siege or Diablo game, and only had a few difficult parts.  While the character's health was generally low and you can only define Katarina as \"squishy,\" the dodging function was exceptionally overpowered.  Once I got a good tempo while playing Katarina, I spent more time dodging than anything else. Due to the game's auto-target system, it was exceptionally easy to dodge, dodge, face in the general direction of your target, shoot, dodge.  While this removed most, if not all, of the difficulty of the game, it added a level of difficulty created by the pure frustration of changing targets.  Once the game selected a target, it was usually counter productive to attempt to change to a more desirable target than it was to simply kill all the least desirable targets to get to your intended target.\nThe second issue was that the story was completely unengaging.\nThe UI was cumbersome, and counterintuitive.\nFinally, the exact way stats affected your character were never defined, leaving the power gamer in me screaming for satisfaction.\nIt's a clear step-down from the original Dungeon Sieges in almost every way, but it is very similar to the Diablo franchise now. The original Dungeon Sieges were hack/slashes, but were party based and unique enough to stand apart.  If you don't have some other game to occupy your time, DS3 is an awesome game. However, don't go in expecting something comparable to DS 1 or 2. Expect another Diablo clone and while it is a pretty good clone, no clone is comparable to the original.", "hours": 11.8, "username": "Shortlived", "products": 214, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 81, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-06-28", "text": "Great story, beautiful visuals, and difficulty is challenging enough on Regular to not get bored.\nIts an excellent hack and slash, action RPG type, and the multiplayer (from what little I experienced) is flawlessly executed.", "hours": 37.5, "username": "LunaticHippy .MurdocK", "products": 359, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 81, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-06-27", "text": "From playing this for an hour and half I got the impression GPG must have walked up to some Russian/Ukrainian Game Dev. students and said here, we will pay you a bit to make us some random cheap\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665game to sell do the DS fans to make lots of quick cash! but oh wait, apparently the game IP of dungeon siege is owned by Square Enix now, so no real surprise there...\nBasically, its a sub standard game. Oh would that steam only had a proper scoring mechanism, but no it takes it's scores from meta critic. :( this was a horrible waste of money.\nAll I can do is 'recommend' the game with the 'handwritten(typed)' score of 2/5 bleah.", "hours": 1.7, "username": "Felix", "products": 258, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 81, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-06-24", "text": "\u9996\u5148\uff0c\u5982\u679c\u4f60\u60f3\u73a9\u8fd9\u6b3e\u6e38\u620f\uff0c\u8bf7\u81ea\u5907\u624b\u67c4\uff0c\u81f3\u5c11\u662f360\u89c4\u683c\u7684\u3002\u7528\u952e\u76d8\u73a9\u5bb9\u6613\u86cb\u788e\u3002\n\u786e\u5b9e\u662f\u5f88\u4e0d\u9519\u7684\u4e00\u6b3e\u4f5c\u54c1\uff0c\u53ef\u4ee5\u7b97\u662fRPG\u7c7b\u7684ACT\uff0c\u56e0\u4e3a\u592a\u8003\u9a8c\u683c\u6321\u548c\u8eb2\u907f\u6280\u5de7\u4e86\uff0c\u7528\u6218\u58eb\u524d\u671f\u6253BOSS\u771f\u7684\u53ea\u6709\u88ab\u4e00\u5957\u79d2\u7684\u6599\uff0c\u6cd5\u5e08\u4ec0\u4e48\u7684\u53ef\u80fd\u66f4\u8106\u3002 \u6240\u4ee5\u6b64\u6b3e\u6e38\u620f\u7684\u96be\u5ea6\u76f8\u5bf9\u6765\u8bf4\u8fd8\u662f\u5f88\u9ad8\u7684\uff0c\u5efa\u8bae\u6253\u7a7f\u8fc7DMC\u7cfb\u5217\u4f5c\u54c1\u7684\u4eba\u518d\u6765\u73a9=-= \u8fd9\u53ef\u548cD3\uff0c T2\u8fd9\u7c7b\u4f20\u7edf\u5237\u5237\u5237\u4e0d\u4e00\u6837\u3002\n\u6e38\u620f\u7684\u4eba\u8bbe\u5f88\u559c\u6b22~ \u5404\u79cd\u517b\u773c\uff0cDLC\u4e5f\u5f88\u6709\u8282\u64cd\u3002\u6069\u5c31\u662f\u8fd9\u6837\u3002\u503c\u5f97\u4e00\u73a9\uff0c\u624b\u6b8b\u614e\u73a9\u3002", "hours": 20.6, "username": "Bethic", "products": 778, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 81, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-06-18", "text": "It's not the greatest game in the world but a PC exclusive patch that came out kinda fixed it a little bit, now it plays nicely but it's still an average game.  It's better though, and kind of addicting!  You should try it if you can grab it on sale.  It's good enough for a sale price.  :)", "hours": 13.2, "username": "XDeadzX", "products": 1013, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 81, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-06-06", "text": "Even though this game is a few years old, the graphics are still crisp. Now, a downside to this game is that there's only one way to really 'fast travel' between locations, and those are limited. Within any given area/city/etc you'll be going back and forth from one end of the map to another multiple times, and the enemies will respawn within a few moments so the maps are never clear of baddies. That aside, the game is still very playable, with easy to pick up controls, a good story and nicely written characters.", "hours": 15.7, "username": "Quietus Wolf", "products": 285, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 82, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-06-05", "text": "This game is more painful than having your ballsack stepped on by an angry Taiwanese hooker and twice as expensive\nso... a pretty good deal really", "hours": 0.2, "user_id": "76561198042600079", "username": "soujiro707", "products": 385, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 82, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-06-05", "text": "console version may be sluggish, but this PC version excels! Loving it.", "hours": 9.5, "username": "Mashuu", "products": 461, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 82, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-06-04", "text": "Did you enjoy Dungeon Siege 1 or 2? Do you like action rpg's like Diablo or Torchlight?  Or you even enjoyed the D&D lite Bauldur's Gate version for console? If you answered yes to any of these questions then don't buy this game.\nWhat DS3 does is a disgrace to aRPG's. What's so strange is it from Obsidian, one of my favorite developers. How they messed this up so badly is beyond my comprehension. Let me point out a few of the flaws.\nCONTROLS - In all aRPG's the left mouse button moves your character around, attacks enemies that are highlighted, and picks up loot. In DS3 the left mouse is the attack key only. It's basically what most games have set as shift+attack since when you press it you stop what you're doing and preform an attack no matter if there's an enemy or not. Moving is the right mouse button. The move button does not attack at all. Picking up items is the 'E' key. Yup, they took one simplistic function and divided it into 3 buttons that will confuse and frustrate you. That's just one example of how badly they messed up the control scheme here.\nCHARACTER - Character development should be an important aspect of any RPG. You are presented with 4 different characters to choose from, all with different abilities, and a decent back story. So in the beginning you're thining you'll be able to develop and grow this person. Nope. Firstly, you are not allowed to zoom in on your character for a close-up look. When you get new weapons and armor their apperance changes, but you can never really get the feel of how much more badass you are. Combine that with the worst inventory management system I've seen in 10 or more years. You are never allowed to view your character in an inventory screen and see good your new loot looks. And if that wasn't enough, when you interact with other characters in the game you are only ever shown the other person's face. Basically once you choose your avatar, and begin the game, you will never be allowed to relate to them again. Match that with a talent tree that doesn't give you a choice as to what to develop. You are forced to unock all abilities in each tier.\nGRAPHICS - There is one major problem here. Peoples eyes look like they are dead. Everyone's eyes in this game is slightly whited out and it seriously feels like they are the eyes of the deceased. Also a problem is the UI. I mentioned some of it with the inventory, but the UI is just bad all around. Not to mention your characters abilities icons aren't very good. They don't do a good job at representing what each ability does.\nSAVE POINTS - Really!? Save points in a game!? It's the 21st century is there anyway we could have just moved past this? Was it in Square Enix's contract to publish this game it had to have Save Points instead of an auto-save feature, check points, manual save? Oh, and when you do save; instead of just selecting the save slot, you must first select the save slot you want and then you have to actually go to the bottom of the screen and press the save button. An unnecessary step and only further points out the bad programing decisions that were made in this games development.\nMULTIPLAYER - Last but certainly not least is MP. You do not bring your avatar into a MP session. You are only allowed to play as one of the Hosts NPC buddies. Yes, playing with friends means you do nothing more than waste your time while your friend gets to complete the game. Which leads me to my final complaint...\nAI - You unlock NPC's in the game that help out on quests. Basically they're the pets of most aRPG's. Except the pets of most aRPG's are vastly better programmed than these human counterparts. They wander around in combat, barely helping at all. In fact, this game would have faired better if they had just not included them. IMHO it feels like they were behind on development and the team never got around to actually fleshing the NPC's out.\nPros - From all that badness there is some good. The story is well written and developed. Voice acting is good. Game runs well.", "hours": 1.8, "username": "Arkan01d", "products": 950, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 82, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-06-04", "text": "How the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 do you mess up cooperative multiplayer so badly?", "hours": 0.3, "username": "ErisMarie", "products": 1236, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 82, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-06-04", "text": "Completey different from dungeon siege 2. Seems geared more towards user friendlyness so the game feels a bit dumbed down. Currently onsale for $3.74 seems like a great price.", "hours": 6.7, "user_id": "76561197960284046", "username": "DL", "products": 438, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 82, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-14", "text": "Similar to Diablo 2/3. Pretty fun, but it gets repetitive after a while.", "hours": 4.9, "username": "Light", "products": 214, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 82, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-04-18", "text": "Incredibly bug-free for an Obsidian game, but it's also rather generic and not terribly compelling compared to their usual offerings. I made it through most of the game enjoying it more than not, but I realized that I wasn't actually looking forward to it between play sessions. I'm not sure if I burned myself out on side quests or it's just mediocre, but I'm guessing some of both. Strangely for an ARPG, seems to be designed with a controller in mind. Only weakly recommended. Unless you've completely exhausted the genre, you can probably find a game in it that does something more interesting to spend your time with.", "hours": 19.7, "username": "vibratoryblurriness", "products": 1184, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 82, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-03-14", "text": "This turned out to be a very solid hack/slash/loot game.  You can choose from 4 solidly different characters.  The combat starts fairly simple (mash attach, use 1 or 2 abilities), but it gets more complex in a really rewarding way.  Each character has 2 combat stances, and each stance has 3 abilities that you get as you level up, plus 3 defensive abilities.  Each ability can also be mastered to unlock a more powerful version of that ability.  You get to distribute a few meaningful upgrades each time you level up.  The entire game was bug free for me in single player.  The graphics were really nice, and the plot was pretty solid (although as with most fantasy games I said \"huh?!\" a couple times).  The looting is good, the inventory and quest systems are good.  The game isn't incredibly long, but for me that was good.  It was about 9 hours for the single player and it really felt like an epic journey.  A few sidequests, but it wasn't bogged down with them.  As I ramble on, I realize that the bottom line for me was \"this game was pretty awesome.\"   I am also a couple hours into the co-op.  Only the person hosting gets to save their character, but as long as you play with the same person, you'll both get to keep your stuff.  Co-op is mostly smooth, but since you have to both be on the same screen, sometimes your partner running off, gets you trapped in a corner.", "hours": 14.8, "username": "atleast0", "products": 1405, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 82, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-03-08", "text": "A surprisingly good game. I picked it up on sale, but I could recommend it at it's current price.", "hours": 30.9, "user_id": "76561197998275901", "username": "God Emperor Trump", "products": 557, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 82, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-03-02", "text": "Fun co-op modes. Somewhat interesting story. To me is not the greateset Dungeon Siege, but I'm telling ya when you play it with friends...it is loads of fun. Check it out if you like the franchise.", "hours": 1.2, "username": "Ravens\\\\", "products": 259, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 83, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-25", "text": "Never played the old games, so i got into it fresh. And let me tell you, is a very good game.\nObsidian quality what else.\nPS: This game as a lot of Babes !\nBest babes in a game, word !", "hours": 40.1, "user_id": "76561198014492379", "username": "Michael Weston", "products": 386, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 83, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-02-12", "text": "I am writing this as a recommendation to STAY AWAY from this title. I thoroughly enjoyed the first two DS tiltes but this one really \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 on the series. The control scheme has been revamped which is okay but the moving camera does it's best to make this unplayable. The targeting system is absolutely horrendous and adds to the already difficult boss fights. I almost never NOT finish a game I start but the stink of console-itis was just too much to bear. It's unfortunate because there's a good game under here.  It looks great and I love loot hunting but the controls and camera are AWFUL. I'm bummed and I hope those who read this don't waste their $$$ on this like I did. Hell, you'd be better off watching the Dungeon Siege movie than playing this. AVOID AVOID AVOID.", "hours": 2.7, "username": "MikeUFC", "products": 1184, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 83, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-04", "text": "game is gay", "hours": 2.2, "user_id": "76561198018803052", "username": "LevelZeroHero", "products": 142, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 83, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-01-28", "text": "Not worth the brand name \"Dungeon Siege\"! Nothing like Dungeon Siege 1 or 2, total disappointment - not even COOP with a friend makes this playable and is pure torture. Hands off, even with 75% sale. Make sure you play the demo first if you still consider it.", "hours": 2.6, "user_id": "76561197963627578", "username": "SnipingCoward", "products": 177, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 83, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-01-26", "text": "Beautiful story, absolutely gorgeous graphics, tons of variety in the way you can play.\nGreat game.", "hours": 38.1, "username": "Germaximus", "products": 469, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 83, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-01-16", "text": "This is a great game, and very game controller friendly.", "hours": 8.0, "username": "Technomender", "products": 182, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 83, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-01-08", "text": "I thought this was going to be\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 but it actually turned out pretty okay. Very different from the predecessors, though. Story is alright and the combat is fun.", "hours": 16.3, "username": "Chandler", "products": 1485, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 83, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-25", "text": "One small step forwards with Dungeon Siege II, one GIGANTIC LEAP backwards-- Into a pit filled with ravenous bugbears, for Dungeon Siege III. How can you take a system that rewards the fluid growth of your character from repetition and decide to just strip away all the customization and talentry that was inherit with it? Whoever though that was a good idea? Fluid character growth is always better than the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 tiered talent system. God damn this game, and god damn the stupid advertisements that flaunted it when it came out. Thank the gods I got it for five dollars.\n3.5/10", "hours": 0.8, "username": "Kaldaris", "products": 330, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 83, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-12", "text": "I didn't finish this but I actually did enjoy it. Although anything that involes square enix runs the risk of giving you aids. 7/10", "hours": 9.4, "username": "sloth", "products": 245, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 83, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-08", "text": "Decent enough, BUT don't expect it to be even remotely simular to DS1 and DS2.  Quite frankly, this isn't Dungeon Siege at all.  It's a console game that they named DS3 and released it to the DS community thinking we might take the bait.  Yes, I did buy it and yes I've played it, but felt so ripped off and disappointed the whole time.", "hours": 74.5, "username": "Warondar", "products": 280, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 84, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-10-20", "text": "Consolized and surprisingly hard. It has a bland story, unsatisfying loot, and it's short for an RPG. At least it's pretty - and bug free.", "hours": 20.7, "username": "Chordian", "products": 266, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 84, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-18", "text": "Console port of a mildly fun RPG-lite with nice graphics, music, and sound, but completely dissimilar to previous Dungeon Siege games and marred by a lousy camera, frustrating controls, and cumbersome interface.", "hours": 18.8, "username": "Sinbad", "products": 2026, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 84, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-10-18", "text": "Terrible co-op. Mediocre dungeon crawling.\nAnd this is coming  from possibly the world's biggest dungeon siege fan.\nStay away unless it's $5.", "hours": 4.9, "username": "Tamriilin", "products": 528, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 84, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-10-12", "text": "This game is a piece of trash. Stay away.", "hours": 0.3, "username": "Vio", "products": 344, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 84, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-04", "text": "In many ways, this is better than Diablo 3.  OMG!  Yes I said it!  It feels like a game made in this decade and not in the 90's.  I could change the camera angle, I played it with a controller, there were actual cutscenes with dialog not just text bubbles, my character talked!  My companions were the other heroes I didn't pick.  I got to shape the world depending on my actions (kill or save a guy, free or imprison another guy, etc) so it had replayability and your choices mattered.  The classes were fun, I played the chick with the gun.  Cool abilities.  Cool story.  The game had different endings.  It's really worth playing and I enjoyed it much more than Diablo 3.   I give this game 4 out of 5 Whitestars.", "hours": 22.3, "username": "Whitestar19", "products": 395, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 84, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-11", "text": "Fun enough for some mindless dungeon crawling until you realise that the game thinks itself an epic tale. Well that throws the mindless fighting out the window. Now I have to pay attention to what people say and go where they tell me -- or work out where the heck they want me to go. Loot drops constantly but it's never realy clear why one item should be chosen over the other, unless the numbers are significantly higher. Costumes never appear to be anything more than palette swaps and remixes of the initial outfit your character comes with. Thus, depending on who's playing, all enemies change the useless clothing which they carry in their pockets to suit who's coming to kill them. How nice! And what kind of loot game lacks a means to examine your character. You have to get the camera jammed in corner so you can see youself properly.", "hours": 5.1, "username": "UberNoodle", "products": 238, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 84, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-01", "text": "Camera and movement controlls are crap!", "hours": 0.2, "username": "west_ninja", "products": 920, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 84, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-08-22", "text": "Nothing like DS1 or 2 at all, in no way. The story suposivly is a much later continuation...that's about it. This game is a prime example of the \"evils\" of current day companys. Designed (forced really) to play multiplayer & carrying nothing over from the franchise roots but name. DS1 and 2 were the creators of a genra like dragonage 1. DS3 is a forced multiplayer hack and slash with poor graphics and a badly done story.", "hours": 1.0, "user_id": "76561197978374804", "username": "Faded Tiger", "products": 651, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 84, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-19", "text": "I beat the crap out of this game and while I may not have gone achievement crazy, this game was definately fun!", "hours": 28.0, "username": "Ettasy", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 84, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-19", "text": "This is the first Dungeon Siege game that I have played and I really did enjoy it.  The story, graphics, fighting, and character customization were all well done.  Unfortunately, for everything this game does right, you will only remember it for what it did wrong... the camera.  This is hands down the most frustrating thing you will encounter outside of a few annoyingly difficult bosses.  The camera angles tend to be almost directly overhead and always seem to rotate around to the worst viewpoint possible.  Maybe the camera is only a coop issue, but be warned.\n7/10", "hours": 29.5, "username": "ritardedartkid", "products": 522, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 85, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-12", "text": "The 3DS~!  I was first in line for this when it became available for download and I do not regret it!  It is 5 gigabytes to download, but it's worth it once you see the awesome 3D effects.  After you download your 3DS, I also recommend getting Mario Kart.  Strangely, while they offer the 3DS on Steam, they do not offer Mario Kart.  I sent an e-mail to Mr. Torvalds about this, but all I got was a form letter about \"FreeBSD\" whatever that is (I think it is an illegal recreational drug).", "hours": 21.5, "username": "Dire Miralis", "products": 318, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 85, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-04", "text": "Nothing to do with Dungeon Siege as we know it. Will seriously annoy fans of DS1+2. It's more Diablo than Dungeon Siege but if you can look past the fact it isnt what it says it is you will find a decent game. 70%", "hours": 73.7, "user_id": "76561197991657927", "username": "MrMuse", "products": 883, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 85, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-02", "text": "not as bad as people say it is", "hours": 2.4, "user_id": "76561197993374835", "username": "moxie", "products": 277, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 85, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-18", "text": "Dungeon Siege III is by no means a great game, particularly in light of the drastic changes that make this entry to the series a sharp departure from its superior predecessors.\nBut that tart treatment is not the whole story. The truth is that DS3 is simply a fun game to play, particularly with friends, even if it's not a very good one. It's quick to pick up, easy to engage and hooks you with the classic ARPG formula: leveling, talents and gear upgrades!\nWith the entire Dungeon Siege franchise bundled for less than $20 these days, it's hard not to come home with this one in tow. Grab some friends and enjoy it for what it is: a simple and enjoyable hack'n'slash.\nVerdict: 7/10", "hours": 5.6, "username": "thraxbert", "products": 388, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 85, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-18", "text": "I can recommend this game for people who are looking for a good single player dungeon crawler. But for those who are looking for a cooperative adventure, don't come here. The coop mode in this game is completely useless, you come in as kind of like a placeholder for the companion you have in the single player. You dont gain levels, or loot, or anything of value, its a one-sided help to the host. The story is decent enough to continue to play for a while, but because of the fact that dungeon crawlers are lonely by nature, the game loses luster unless you are completely commited to the game. If you really want to play the game get it. But not at full price.", "hours": 8.9, "username": "rev_lution", "products": 357, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 85, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-17", "text": "un exellent RPG que je recomande a tous", "hours": 22.7, "username": "gaspettes au grand coeur", "products": 580, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 85, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-07-17", "text": "Dont waste your money.\nDungeon Siege 3 sucks.", "hours": 3.0, "username": "H. Harpoon", "products": 693, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 85, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-07-17", "text": "this game sucks horrible amounts of\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665", "hours": 1.3, "username": "Bozworth", "products": 623, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 85, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-17", "text": "I hate the way this game got a load of flak in reviews. Absolutely brilliant game and it's a decent challenge as well.", "hours": 32.0, "user_id": "76561198004609618", "username": "Narj", "products": 185, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 85, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "If you're a fan of Dungeon Siege 1 and 2, this game isn't even remotely the same. It was sold by Gas Powered Games (DS1/DS2 creators) by Chris Taylor and Square Enix were the buyers.\nObsidian Entertainment butchered the style of Dungeon Siege entirely, but they obviously couldn't have been trying to use anything more than a similar lore basis.\nIgnoring the relation to the previous two games, this isn't actually a bad game in it's own right. It's got a decent story and a decent combat system, though it's entirely designed for consoles and simply given a decent PC port.\nWhile it doesn't re-invent anything, it's a solid title if you get it on a Steam sale for under 7$. It gives roughly 20 hours of gameplay, and the DLC adds another 2 hours or so as well. More gameplay if you replay it to try out each character, as you can only play that one character, even though you recruit all 4 throughout the game. All 4 character clears would be around 60+ Hours of gameplay.", "hours": 24.0, "username": "Kahran Ramsus", "products": 847, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 86, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "Don't buy this game. Whatever redeeming parts of the last installments in the series are gone, leaving only the most content-thin, generic, and boring of RPGs.", "hours": 0.4, "username": "Archdrake", "products": 1433, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 86, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "Fun lil action RPG. Love Reinhart! Expansion is a must, it adds respec'ing, new ability gems, tons of new content, and items. Well worth the investment. <3 Obsidian.", "hours": 0.5, "username": "Bats", "products": 2075, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 86, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-07-15", "text": "This game pales in comparision to the original Dungeon Sieges, and doesn't do them justice. The game is boring and the plot is contrived. It tries to be Diablo and fails. It never kept me interested.\nMany other recent RPGs have done much better (Skyrim, Witcher 2, Diablo 3, etc), and I suggest you take a look at those and avoid buying this.", "hours": 2.4, "username": "Soundyman", "products": 687, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 86, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-15", "text": "Follow my curation :\nNot half bad as the reviews... enjoyable RPG", "hours": 17.0, "username": "exorio", "products": 505, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 86, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "This game is really underrated in my opinion, but it's only good if you approach it as less of an action-RPG and more of a story-based RPG. I thoroughly enjoy it, and that's really all I can say about it.", "hours": 140.1, "username": "Countess Isolde", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 86, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-26", "text": "really freaky stuff. At one point I was fighting Witches in Latex. Da\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665did I just play ?!", "hours": 49.1, "username": "Adi", "products": 170, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 86, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-09", "text": "Although the story is weak, the art and gameplay are quite nice.", "hours": 32.3, "username": "Little Sparrow", "products": 316, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 86, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-08", "text": "Great game engine that runs smoooooth. Graphics are colorful and crisp. Gameplay very much a Diablo clone. Upgrades and perks are 'ok' but nothing special. If you like Diablo it's a must play.", "hours": 18.5, "user_id": "76561198059068031", "username": "e_sanders25", "products": 104, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 86, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-07", "text": "Really enjoyed this game, although it didnt risen to the previous 2 games; graphics are spectacular for a h'n's, the light/fire effects are amazing, the music is great (the voiceacting is almost terrible). The h'n's mechanics are pretty good, there is plenty of loot, story is interesting and gameplay varies due to the 4 different classes. But somehow i got almost always a feeling of artificiallity or better put lack of life in the game's world, this pulling down the atmosphere.", "hours": 14.8, "username": "Lolozaur", "products": 2395, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 86, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-05", "text": "With Diablo 3 around the corner, figured I should play this game otherwise I never would.  Not a bad game in general, but it suffers greatly due to the fact that this game was made with consoles in mind.  Sure you can at least customize graphics (to a basic extent) but for some reason you cannot customize controls and the default keyboard mouse controls are just terrible.  Instead of having abilities 1-6 binded its 1-3 and you have to continually hit shift to switch to other abilities which basicly means you aren't going to be dodging or blocking (space) when you need to.  Plugged in a controller and suddenly everything made sense and I stopped dying every 2 seconds because i could actually play.  The decision making, combat and story are actually decent, all else aside.  Buy it for cheap, or just wait for Diablo 3 or Torchlight 2 if you like dungeon crawlers, and you might as well buy on console if you have one since the pc version is probably worse than it without a controller.", "hours": 20.4, "username": "Thanatov", "products": 408, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 87, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-03", "text": "If you were a fan of the original Dungeon Siege, you're probably too busy with work, nightlife, bills, and studying to have even noticed this baddy touchdown on shelves.\nIt's been years since we last battled the epic final bosses of Dungeon Siege II- Bhad Kamurah and Lyag. You'll find it a nostalgic treat to know that Bhad Kamurah makes a return to the series in Dungeon Siege III as a consistant enemy! You'll have to come up with innovative and sometimes creative strategies to work your way to victory over this old foe! As if that wasn't enough, each and every level is made unique by a curse mysteriously named Porr Diizine! It is up to you, the heroes of the kingdom of Ehb to figure out how to rid the lands of this evil plague or forever remain lost and confused by it!", "hours": 2.4, "user_id": "76561197996067505", "username": "\u2655Dean Da God", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 87, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-02", "text": "Play this game if you want to break your fingers on the keyboard.\nThis game became fun only after the hours I spent programming a Logitech G13 gaming keyboard to keep my fingers from tying into knots.\nSome of the supporting abilities are very weak.  It's possible to build a character that can't progress beyond a boss and becomes stuck.  There are plenty of save points; make a lot of new saves.\nReading texts in game is terribly executed.  I keep telling myself I'll read them later in the Lore menu.\nThe visuals are pretty but the settings are finicky.  Adequately controlling the camera requires a thumbstick.  Fighting and moving the camera together can easily require 5 simultaneous keystrokes.\nI mute the music and listen to a playlist of my favorite bands.\nI really enjoyed DS1 and DS2 with all their expansions and Broken Sword.\nThis game made me yell a few times.\nAfter slapping it around a few times with the G13 I feel that tender Dungeon Siege attraction.", "hours": 46.4, "username": "PitBrat", "products": 210, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 87, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-04-20", "text": "Uh... I dunno. It's okay. DS 2 made a much bigger splash for me. The controls are VERY uncomfortable, and not at all intuitive. To whit: this game is uber-consolized. Not as bad as Fable 3 (*sigh*), and not completely unplayable. Just verey obviously meant to be played with a console controller.\nThe story lives up to the series, the graphics are \"good,\" the controls are... they're really pretty bad. Again, not unplayable. Just counter-intuitive. The levelling system is different from either of the first two games, which is okay.\nI don't know why, but I'm really feeling bitter about DS3 at this point. It just wasn't as good as its predecessors. That seems to be a theme with gaming franchises recently.\n[UPDATE]\nAfter playing Torchlight 2, I'm never touching this piece of\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665again.", "hours": 17.5, "username": "thorvindr", "products": 410, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 87, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-10", "text": "Just finnished this game and DLC with someone else. This game has an really really good stoyline, good voice acting for all of the quests, good look along with tons of items to loot. The most eye catching aspect about this game is that as you play this game you have to make choices that effect how the story plays out. Usualy the choices have to do with someone's fate or what action should be taken. Combined with the voice acting this is very impressive. Over all a really good RPG game, looking forward to the other DLC that is sure to come for this game.\nThe only down sides is that it is not what I would call an open world and in multi-player the \"3 legged race\" feel with the camara takes getting used too. But if you ignore thoes two things this is a game that is worth you time. Fully say to anyone who likes the screen shots to get this game.\nBTW..... Got 57% of the achivements, see if you can beat that.", "hours": 40.1, "username": "Vy'jul'k", "products": 256, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 87, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-01", "text": "This is a must for all RPG fans. Adventure and fun factor is top notch.", "hours": 32.0, "username": "Chaz", "products": 1722, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 87, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-04-01", "text": "Wow what a piece of\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665...Never underestimate the ability of large corporations collaborating together to churn out a steaming pile of filth.  The basic camera issues and glitches would more than fill out a review before the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665rpg elements and boring game play could even be discussed.  \"O you mean to tell me that every single move I get can be mastered and then empowered to create a unique variant of that same move?!\"....cool now I have total of 5 moves when I beat the game...and maybe 2 of them are useful.  Riveting.    The graphics are dated,  the camera sucks a huge phallus (especially on multiplayer which is what the game is meant for, unless of course you enjoy running around with an  A.I  imitating Gilbert Grape), and the combat gets stale after 2 hours.  Thankfully the game can be completed in around 10 so I can assure you, if you already made the mistake of purchasing, the suffering will be brief.  I\u2019d rather go to church than play through this game again.  2/10  Doodie.", "hours": 41.5, "user_id": "76561197996412022", "username": "Stormcleave", "products": 199, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 87, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-01", "text": "the game is great although there are ppl that say its fun okay or bad. this is my opinion. ds3 is different from ds1 and ds2 because of different gameplay. ds1-2 was more like a basic action rpg game like dragon age, fable or kingdoms of amalar. ds3 resemble a bit of the diablo combat system with its own feel to it. this what cause ppl to complain saying its a terrible diablo clone. like i said its a different feel and not suppose to copy diablo. the graphics are beatiful and voice acting is very good in this. even though they say story line is short approx 12-14 hours thats just 1 person. if u want play each one to know how they affect the story in the game and there background. really reccomend this if your looking for a good rpg to play.", "hours": 20.5, "user_id": "76561198042684091", "username": "Samaron12", "products": 347, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 87, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-27", "text": "DS1: Awsome DS2: Amazing DS3: Total Trash, Every time I force myself to play it I die alittle inside.", "hours": 0.8, "username": "smok3", "products": 517, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 87, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-26", "text": "game sucks...\np.s.     oi", "hours": 13.5, "user_id": "76561197994337864", "username": "BUBBY", "products": 260, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 87, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-26", "text": "Played the demo, wasn't 1/2 bad. DO NOT BUY unless its on sale. just torrent this \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 otherwise.", "username": "M4j1k N1nj4", "products": 453, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 88, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-26", "text": "Dungeon Siege III is a decent RPG, as you would expect from Obsidian Entertainment. But if you've played the previous Dungeon Siege games, you will notice the way it plays is much different. In my opinion it is much better, but some people will find it off putting to find such dramatic change. The storyline is good, if confusing. Combat takes a little getting used to, as the control scheme is a bit weird. As most Dungeon Siege games go, it's a good game if a bit unpolished. Wait until it's on sale.", "hours": 24.9, "username": "NorskVind", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 88, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-25", "text": "lmfao hahaha this game sucks", "hours": 0.4, "username": "fairly fucking insanely stupid", "products": 279, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 88, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-25", "text": "This game is actually a pretty solid RPG. I feel that the 72 out of 100 rating is a little harsh, but i enjoyed playing the role of the mage and also found the main quest and side quest entertaining for the most part. I recommend buying, especially if it is on SALE and you like RPG's.   4 out of 5", "hours": 7.5, "username": "BurninDownDank", "products": 549, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 88, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-25", "text": "Wouldnt touch this with a 10 foot barge pole. DSI was amazing, DS2 was average. This is NOT DS...", "hours": 11.5, "username": "Snapfrozen", "products": 185, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 88, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-05", "text": "Nothing alike the previous DS titles + handles much better w a gamepad. Ally AI is stupid (but u can solo thnkfully) and the co-op works in a weird way (camera + saves) but u get used 2 it eventually. Other than that this is a solid title. Tech looks impressive and is 100% stable + the story & dialogue options are suprisingly good 4 a H&S title; desicions influence parts of the game. Combat mechanics are also good and force u to be constantly active (must block | roll 24/7, mana regens on hit,etc).Loot diversity could be better uniques look awesome however. Each of the 4 chars plays diffirently and the game is sadistically hard on Hardcore diff. All in all if you want a co-op based, challenging H&S title with engaging combat, great visuals and an interesting story then this is right up your alley.", "hours": 48.9, "username": "Chi||969", "products": 2056, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 88, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-16", "text": "Developed by Obsidian and published by Square Enix; Dungeon Siege 3 is a very good action loot oriented rpg. Streamlined compared to it's predecessors but surprisingly polished and littered with the influence of Square. The original penned yarn and accompanied lore are well versed and played out through npc interaction and discovery.  The game's art direction and lighting are striking and the voice acting is suffcient.  The companion AI, one choosen from a set of 3 as the story evolves, can be customized though not directly controlled and can be swapped but not during combat. Skill trees have been replaced with an abilitiy / profiency system though this system does not provide the level of customization seen in similiar games with extensive skill trees. To compensate for the lack of health or mana potions mana regen occurs though battle and health regen occurs though the use of abilities.  PC controls have been long since patched but the controller implementation is near perfect.", "hours": 45.8, "username": "Sysgen", "products": 6142, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 88, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-15", "text": "Very meh, uninstalled it after an hour or two of play. Generic predetermined classes with what felt like a generic story.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "VehoNex", "products": 460, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 88, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-02-14", "text": "Only 10 hours of gameplay, and no character customization. Stack that with horrible controls and this game should be sent to the bargain bin.", "hours": 22.4, "user_id": "76561198014628604", "username": "RoboGerbil", "products": 260, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 88, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-02-09", "text": "worst in the series", "hours": 2.9, "username": "Feenster", "products": 294, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 88, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-01-10", "text": "Dungeon Siege was awesome, Dungeon Siege II was ok, Dungeon Siege III is a disappointment and does not resemble anything that made the first Dungeon Siege great.", "hours": 0.8, "username": "Pullo", "products": 398, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 89, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-07", "text": "A fairly standard hack'n'slash dungeon crawl with solid mechanics, fun combat, and boring loot. Haven't tried the multiplayer yet. Not much replayability.", "hours": 18.8, "username": "Vino [Olive Garden]", "products": 1168, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 89, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-31", "text": "Standard fare for dungeon-crawling RPGs. Fun combat, decent loot, cool characters, even cooler moves, but oh for the love of God don't even bother with it if you don't have a gamepad because the keyboard controls are absolutely atrocious.", "hours": 30.5, "username": "Pretty Little Songbird!", "products": 170, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 89, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-12-30", "text": "worst game ever, dont buy it like i did\nThe items are all the same.\nYou cannot customize your characters.\nThe cameras are all weird.\nThe siegelets which made the game awesome were removed", "hours": 2.3, "username": "Navy Seal.pt", "products": 846, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 89, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-29", "text": "This is a very solid action RPG title. There might not be as much custom character choice as is in the Diablo series, but the story, good looking visuals, ambient and great music make up for it.", "hours": 14.8, "user_id": "76561198008414102", "username": "DamZe", "products": 272, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 89, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "This game does a lot right.  The combat system is really refreshing.  However, the loot is boring and it's really hard to \"respec\".  The story and setting are pretty generic RPG fare.  Although this is an ok game, there are so many better options that it's hard to recommend this one.", "hours": 22.2, "username": "EightDrunkenGods", "products": 248, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 89, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "Might be hard to get used to if you played the first and the second Dungeon Siege game, but it's worth it. We follow an amazing story while being surrounded by a fantastic environment with amazingly done creatures and characters.\nAs an artist, this game really does inspire me to open up Photoshop and start working!", "hours": 27.6, "user_id": "76561198036240160", "username": "Zariga", "products": 466, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 89, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "dont buy this game for pc! it might be great on console but it was never designed for pc and they put no effort into making it a pc game.", "hours": 1.9, "user_id": "76561198003530837", "username": "Airyk21", "products": 372, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 89, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "If you haven't played any of the previous games and you enjoy Gauntlet style combat then you MIGHT enjoy this game.\nHowever, having played the first two games in the series I am greatly disappointed. Square Enix not only destroyed the mechanics that defined the Dungeon Siege series but they also did a great deal of damage to the setting as well. Everything is completely different. As such I was greatly disappointed. there is little to no back tracking available in the game, if you miss completing a quest you cannot go back and do it without starting a new game.\nAlso the game didnt take much skill at all to beat.", "hours": 27.0, "username": "Russian Mike", "products": 346, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 89, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-23", "text": "IS OKAY... 3.5/5.0 STAR I GIVE.. KEEP ME OCCUPY FOR 48HOUR...", "hours": 11.2, "user_id": "76561198029959851", "username": "unseen_83", "products": 478, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 89, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-22", "text": "geniales Spiel aber sau schwer", "hours": 7.7, "user_id": "76561197992306644", "username": "OptikBooom", "products": 232, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 90, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-16", "text": "This should be titled: \"Dungeon Siege 3: Obsidian needs a paycheck\" Boring and Bland Diablo clone.  I bought it for $5 and I still feel dirty.", "hours": 2.1, "username": "Rah", "products": 1101, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 90, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-04", "text": "A fun, if relatively simple, hack 'n slash game. Lots of character customization, a well-done atmosphere, and nice graphics. Definitely a huge leap up from the first two games and lots of fun.", "hours": 6.6, "username": "GDwarf", "products": 734, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 90, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-12-02", "text": "I wrote a pretty anger fueled review on this in the past, only because I really was expecting a game like their previous titles, but I can't even begin expressing my disappointment in this game. I know I have only played for about an hour and I would love to try and play it again now that I have actually gotten alot older since (I was still in High school and now im 22 so you can see the age gap), but I can not bring myself to actually play it since I remember how\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665I was, so I am going to just highly recommend you play the previous dungeon sieges (keep in mind they could run on Windows 98 so its pretty old but they are still a hell of alot more funner than what I remember from this game, idk I have nothing else to say other than, they \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ed loyal fans hard", "hours": 1.2, "username": "\u266b Wub Master J \u266b", "products": 340, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 90, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-06", "text": "very nice game, really worth buying the complete edition...", "hours": 18.2, "username": "Vivastar", "products": 406, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 90, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-05", "text": "A simplistic RPG that allows co-op play, is a fun pick up and play RPG like the others, is just a little more console orientated.", "hours": 0.0, "user_id": "76561197985072747", "username": "FantasyFreak_UK", "products": 1243, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 90, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-25", "text": "It's an OK single player game.  It has nothing to do with Dungeon Siege 1 or 2 other than the name.  Don't pay more then $10 for this game.", "hours": 19.9, "username": "TheSilverHammer", "products": 472, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 90, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-24", "text": "Obsidian is at the helm here for Dungeon Siege 3, not Gas Powered Games. DS3 has improved in some regards, yet went backwards in others.\nFor improvements, DS3 has the best story & characters this series has ever offered-up. Another improvement is that there are quests which have more than 1 solution to them.\nThere are issues, though - the camera can be wonky & wind-up poorly placed. The game lacks the size of parties, which basically made the previous titles what they are. Pretty much, there is only you & a NPC [which you have no control over] going with you in your SP campaign. All the strategy elements of DS1 and DS2: Broken World are gone. Forget MP - pretty much nobody is playing this online currently [10/24/2011].\nTake the improvements & also the fact there's plenty of loot to pick-up & skills to upgrade for your character to obtain, this should still certainly keep you playing. Obsidian has overall delivered a solid ARPG experience here w/ DS3.\nGrade: C+", "hours": 30.3, "username": "MysterD", "products": 1948, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 90, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-23", "text": "As far as an RPG goes, The elments are all there. The player progression is very in depth and very well suited to created a very personalized character. Though dialouge leaves much to be disired, the gameplay is very original. The storyline is kinda run-of-the-mil though.\nDon't expect much story, but the RPG of the game is great  -  I'd say wait for a sale like i did and its worth it.", "hours": 1.7, "username": "vfskxxs", "products": 228, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 90, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-21", "text": "Its pretty cool", "hours": 11.3, "username": "Damn.Ninja", "products": 288, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 90, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-17", "text": "Good story line and great graphics, but never finished the final battle as it got too boring.\n6.5 out of 10 rating.", "hours": 132.0, "user_id": "76561197970470181", "username": "Hawk318", "products": 55, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 91, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-10", "text": "Ok, so my first reaction was \"What a complete and utter\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665game!\"\nThen i took a break, and got back and played a few more hours, and it was still\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665but better.\nNow i've played about 9 hours and i'm starting to like it. Yes still many weird design choices, but somehow now it draws me back. I love \"diablo clones\" or loot games, and this all of a sudden works well. Companions are a nice touch. It feels weird to suddenly enjoying it, when the first and second impression was so bad.", "hours": 12.0, "username": "obitom", "products": 1803, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 91, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-09", "text": "A normal game , normal story and normal gameplay. Not so bad and not good.\nIf you like Dungeon Siege 1 & 2 , dont buy this game. You will be disappointed.", "hours": 15.7, "username": "Reimu Maga", "products": 2990, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 91, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-03", "text": "Pros:\nExcellent graphics\nDeep and fun storyline\nExcellent voice acting on almost all npc's\nCreative and fun skills, abilities and execution of them\nCons:\nImpossible to play without gamepad (smooth as silk with one though)\nCan only use one companion at a time (sigh)\nNot much in gear visual changes when getting new equipment (weapon only noticeble visual change when upgrading)\nOverall still worth the play just for the characters and storyline. Just really miss the feel of having that group of characters at one time. Choosing just one companion for situations feels so limiting. Excited to keep playing through which has been rare for me lately on other games.", "hours": 30.3, "user_id": "76561197965180048", "username": "[GTribe] Dark13cloud", "products": 1751, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 91, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-03", "text": "I was hoping for a sequal to dungeon siege 1 or 2. But as it turns out this game has nearly nothing to do with the previous games. It's more like a cheap version of darksiders. The graphics are nice, it has some good combat action, though I liked the versatility of DS1 more. It's a pity that in DS3 most enemies look like clones, all the same faces. And there is no diablo like loot system or a goal where you try to get good gear to showing, use or trade with friends, in fact the coop option is truely limited, but those who log in are forced to stay in the same screen as the host, so no wandering off and they cannot bring their own characters, gear and so on. The only thing they can do is use a free character slot on the host. So they don't gain anything for the time they spend on it. At least not for their own campaign. It's a pity really that they called it DS3, I can only hope there will be a real sequel for DS1 someday in the future.", "hours": 22.9, "username": "Mytharox", "products": 4295, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 91, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-02", "text": "This is a game that reminds us why certain games do better on PC and not on console due to their specific genre related contents. Unlike Dungeon Siege I and II, this game is no where near what it could've been. Anyone who played Dragon Age Origin and then played Dragon Age II would immediately realize that a game that is built to be big, beautiful and content intensive should be put on pc only. Dragon Age II's epic failure proved why DA II should've been on PC. This game, in an attempt to please the console players (like DA II), is a port that failed to provided the mentioned contents, that PC players would otherwise expect. In other words:\nTHIS GAME IS AN EPIC FAILURE IN THE FRANCHISE THAT WE KNOW AS DUNGEON SIEGE. If you see a very low price drop, get it. Otherwise, save your money.", "hours": 24.2, "username": "R\u00ed\u03baud\u00f6u H\u00ee\u03ba\u00f3 S\u0113\u00ecjur\u00f6", "products": 2534, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 91, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-30", "text": "Really sucked before the keybinding update. It was fairly obvious to see this was a console port to the pc. I hope to hell they fixed it...", "hours": 1.3, "username": "t1gershark", "products": 535, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 91, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-29", "text": "This game is fun for those who's into Torchlight, Diablo & Bastion games. nothing ground breaking but still a good game to play alone so please do not play this on Co-op or it will meet your doom.", "hours": 14.9, "username": "\u0307M\u0307\u0398\u0398\u0198I\u03a3 Mookie", "products": 1460, "found_funny": 8, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 91, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-23", "text": "So far this is great and best of all: \"Uncomplicated\" It has ***** in my book so far so good...", "hours": 61.0, "user_id": "76561198029264722", "username": "mcmechau", "products": 375, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 91, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-17", "text": "Great game, a bit short bit has room for addon from DLC. Multiplayer is cool... have yet to have four people max play.", "hours": 40.9, "user_id": "76561197994465477", "username": "TeflonRhino", "products": 199, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 91, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-10", "text": "It may not be true to its roots but it's beautiful and fun:", "hours": 15.8, "username": "Tchad-Like", "products": 2660, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 92, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-07", "text": "Although short I find this game to be visually appealing and a good challenge when it comes to \"boss fights\".", "hours": 8.2, "user_id": "76561198004291725", "username": "Count_of_Acadia", "products": 92, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 92, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-03", "text": "It's the best Diablo-like experience I had in years (since Titan Quest). It plays really smoothly, landscapes and enemies change constantly, every other room you find/buy better gear for yourself and your companion, the game is also quite a looker! A single playthrough took me about 35 hours so that's also quite nice for a modern title. Different classes are very...different - I finished the game with a warrior, now I'm replaying it with Lara Croft (a rogue who uses double pistols) and it's already something else.\nNow for the warnings: it's consolised so make sure you play it using a 360 gamepad because it sucks with mouse and keyboard (I'm a PC gamer at heart but this didn't bother me at all, in fact a pad is implemented really good - all the menus function great, there are useful shortcuts too), it's also very different than the prequels so just treat it as a new title with no expectations ok? All in all it's very arcady - that's why I love it! That's all, quite a pleasant surprise!", "hours": 39.4, "username": "[New Year] Palpek", "products": 1551, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 92, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-08-22", "text": "I bought it and played it for about 11 hours before being completely tired of the monontonous click and kill method to this game. It didn't even have the same appeal other hack n slash'ers have had for me. This game would be worth about $19.99. I'd suggest waiting for it to fall to that price and then picking it up. This is just another reminder of how far Square Enix has fallen from what it was at the end of the 20th century.", "hours": 11.3, "user_id": "76561198011886423", "username": "Archaic", "products": 46, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 92, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-09", "text": "Sweet game. Very awesome visuals if you've got a DX10/DX11 supported graphics card. Kinda different from the first 2 Dungeon Siege games, but it's rich in DS lore & has an awesome storyline. Each playable character has their own background, own playstyles and tactics, & npc's can relate differently to you depending on which one you chose. Definitely the kind of SP game you can put a lot of hours into! :)", "hours": 68.6, "username": "Cyb3rjackal-RWG", "products": 290, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 92, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-08-06", "text": "\u306f\u3063\u304d\u308a\u8a00\u3063\u3066\u540d\u5012\u308c\u3002\u300cDungeon Siege\u300d\u3092\u51a0\u3057\u3066\u307b\u3057\u304f\u306a\u3044\u3002\n\u904e\u53bb\u30b7\u30ea\u30fc\u30ba\u306e\u3044\u3044\u3068\u3053\u308d\u304c\u3059\u3079\u3066\u53d6\u308a\u6255\u308f\u308c\u3066\u304a\u308a\u3001Dungeon Siege\u30c6\u30a4\u30b9\u30c8\u306e\u30c0\u30f3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\u63a2\u7d22\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u3002\n\u5bb6\u5ead\u7528\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u6a5f\u304c\u7d61\u3093\u3067\u304f\u308b\u3068\u3053\u3053\u307e\u3067\u9762\u767d\u304f\u306a\u304f\u306a\u308b\u304b\u3068\u3044\u3046\u3044\u3044\u4f8b\u3060\u3002\nUI\u304c\u7cde\u3002\u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u30e1\u30a4\u30af\u3082\u7cde\u3002\u4e16\u754c\u306e\u8a55\u4fa1\u304c\u4f4e\u304b\u3063\u305f\u610f\u5473\u304c\u3088\u304f\u308f\u304b\u308b\u4f5c\u54c1\u3002\n\u4ed6\u306b\u904a\u3076\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u304c\u3042\u308b\u306a\u3089\u3042\u3048\u3066\u3084\u308b\u5fc5\u8981\u3082\u306a\u3044\u3002", "hours": 87.0, "username": "[=FWS=] TAD", "products": 645, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 92, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-02", "text": "If you're a fan of The Dark Alliance series or The Champions of Norrath games you'll enjoy this. Especially with a controller it feels just like one of those great action rpgs with lots of loot and a really good ranged class that works very well for once.", "hours": 35.9, "username": "JDS", "products": 879, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 92, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-31", "text": "Lets just say that this game wasn't worth the $0 I paid for it.", "hours": 0.2, "username": "polish tarzan", "products": 193, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 92, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-30", "text": "I dont recommend this game at all! It has nothing to do with Ehb or anything part one and part two were about.  It's a shame they used the name Dungeon Siege..", "hours": 1.3, "username": "Serlyhn D'haerkferin", "products": 83, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 92, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-30", "text": "DS3 is a weird one. It has no right to bear \"Dungeon Siege\" in its title and is an obvious console port, yet it somehow redeems itself by the end when you realize that it's more-or-less a proper RPG masquerading as H&S. Moral choices and other major decisions and not something you usually find in the aforementioned genre nor is lengthy epilog detailing the consequences of your decisions. Unexpected thumbs up.", "hours": 31.1, "username": "Arbiter Libera", "products": 2316, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 92, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-29", "text": "I liked this gave very much until the moment I realized this game is not replayable. There is no +new no way to continue develop you character after you complete the game. Still the game has great sound and great graphics. I think they are much better that titan quest. But titan quest still owns this game because is so much replayable. If you have 50usd to spare and live dungeon crawlers give this one a try. I have not tried the coop yet.", "hours": 31.0, "username": "zatone", "products": 6214, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 93, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-29", "text": "Dungeo Siege 3 is a nice game... However it's limited to only 4 different character... No option to create your own character... DS3 is original but very different from the first two parts... I prefer Dungeon Siege 2 still over DS3 ... ...", "hours": 40.8, "username": "Manimal T. Hunter", "products": 102, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 93, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-07-28", "text": "It's kinda bad, especially compared to the last two. Looting is terrible, multiplayer isn't worth the time considering only the host makes any progress (srsly? wtf?) The last two games had persistant multiplayer. I also don't like that they split all the gear into seperate characters. It just seemed really unneccessary, and limiting the fun of half the game. (Shiney loot.) Controls are pretty bad too, but you get used to them. Character acting is bland and the story is uninteresting, and re-tracking through the same area several times is just boring. I found myself more grinding my teeth than having fun. I've tried to give it a chance a few times, now I'm just sorry I bought it. Maybe if you're really desperate for an new RPG, pick this up. Otherwise, go play something else.", "hours": 1.1, "username": "TactiCat", "products": 489, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 93, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-26", "text": "a LOT better than the reviews say. i love this game.", "hours": 19.3, "username": "henrylin22", "products": 2010, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 93, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-26", "text": "\u3061\u3087\u3063\u3068\u524d\u307e\u3067\u65e5\u672c\u8a9e\u5316\u3057\u3066\u305f\u306e\u306b\u30b9\u30af\u30a8\u30cb\u306e\u305b\u3044\u3067\u3067\u304d\u306a\u304f\u306a\u3063\u305f\u3000\u305b\u3063\u304b\u304f\u8cb7\u3063\u305f\u306e\u306b\u697d\u3057\u3081\u306a\u3044\uff01\u3080\u304b\u3064\u304f\uff01\uff01\uff01", "hours": 14.8, "user_id": "76561198003286783", "username": "Tikuwa@", "products": 583, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 93, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-25", "text": "Excellent game to play, good story and game play. Big lack of multiplayer games available, there is only one or two at any given time open for public play.", "hours": 21.7, "username": "[CVG]Anton", "products": 292, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 93, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-07-13", "text": "If Diablo and Dungeon Siege had a baby this is what it would be like.", "hours": 1.2, "username": "C\u00b2", "products": 1344, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 93, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-11", "text": "7/10. If you are a fan of DS and DS2, this is not the same game. Disappointing in that regard, however, with a game pad, it is not bad. Between 25 to 30 hours of play with 4 selectable characters. Replayability is so-so. Really wanted to give the game a 5/10 due to requiring me to spend $30 for a gamepad, but.. Hopefully, they will fix the controls or permit customization with a later patch.", "hours": 29.3, "user_id": "76561198037472785", "username": "Shalun", "products": 689, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 93, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-09", "text": "This game is nothing like its predecessors, but it's amazing in its own right. There are so many different choices to make, so many different outcomes, a free-form hack-and-slash type of combat system, and so much lore that it can make your head spin. If you are a fan of deeply engaging stories, then this is definitely a game to try. You can play through as one of four main characters, getting the rest as partners along the way, each with their own attitudes, fighting styles, and things they agree with. You can switch between your partners at will, and they add to the story as you play through, with different pieces of insight or comments they make. The gear is completely random, but not overly terrible. There is also a nice multi-player feature where you can host your own private game or join in a public one, although you only have access to the gear the owner has acquired (as it is their game you're playing). All in all, a fantastic game with a lot of lore and plenty of replay value.", "hours": 14.9, "username": "Carmesi|SWG", "products": 570, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 93, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-09", "text": "Good dungeon crawler game with decent story,  graphics good and framerate seems good, worth a play at least once if played the other dungeon sieges although does not grab you in the same way the first two games did.", "hours": 2.1, "username": "Demonslayer2222", "products": 768, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 93, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-07", "text": "Decent story, fantastic visuals and expected action-RPG gameplay - just make sure to use a gamepad!  Until they patch in better PC controls.", "hours": 25.1, "username": "Isidorius", "products": 868, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 94, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-06", "text": "Una campa\u00f1a con una trama sumamente interesante y profunda, rejugable, visualmente poderoso y muy divertido.", "hours": 33.9, "user_id": "76561198016602311", "username": "Beliartxu", "products": 332, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 94, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-04", "text": "Love it!!", "hours": 21.5, "username": "JamesJB", "products": 270, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 94, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-04", "text": "I liked this game very much, it's not like the previous Dungeon Siege games at all and may be if you are a big fan of these series you wouldn't appreciate it as my as a new player to this franchise, but still it's quite interesting and exciting dungeon crawler.", "hours": 20.0, "username": "Lost Hashishin", "products": 1552, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 94, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "#1 wuz better yenno what im sayin", "hours": 4.1, "username": "Dark Magician", "products": 290, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 94, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Is not like a Dungeon Crawler really, but still fun to me.", "hours": 29.4, "username": "Strothman", "products": 1802, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 94, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-02", "text": "Three of the four classes have very interesting naratives and combat styles.  The game as a whole is more suited to consoles and the mouse+keyboard controls are very lacking.  Much better with a gamepad, might be best just to get in on your console.", "hours": 26.9, "username": "OmegaJeff", "products": 454, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 94, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-01", "text": "first 1 stil the best", "hours": 18.6, "username": "spudtnik169", "products": 43, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 94, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-01", "text": "It's a lot of fun, although it does suffer from consolitis.  Best played with a USB controller if you have one.  The story and gameplay is really fun though.", "hours": 13.9, "username": "VA1N", "products": 589, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 94, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-01", "text": "This game had beautiful graphics to it but that is honestly about the extent of it. The game was VERY short for the price tag that the company was asking for it. I would ask around 19.99 for this game and that is being generous. It had a great story line that ended all to quickly unlike the past dungeon sieges that kept you playing for hours. This game can be gone through in less than one day without breaks easily. The controls were absolutely horrible!!!! I did not get used to the controls up until almost the end of the game. For someone looking to blow some money for nothing it is great. For someone looking for a really great hard core game you can enjoy for many hours, It is NOT for you.", "hours": 30.6, "username": "DazzBoomer", "products": 55, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 94, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-30", "text": "SP is mediocre at best with its boring leveling system and attempt at making a good story line in a series that has never focused on SP or story prior to this installment.\nSomething was taken from my friends and I with the release of this game.\nwe used to be able to spend entire weekends Smashing thru goblin caves and leveling our characters as we see fit.\nnow we are congested to the same camera as if we were still playing some Gauntlet game for nintendo 64, and re-issuing our points each time our generic cookie cutter characters die.\nSquare was once my favorite game Dev. Now they are a publisher known for defficating all-over good game series and hopefully dont put thier hands in just cause 3 and Arkham city.", "hours": 4.4, "user_id": "76561197990428993", "username": "Murf The Mouth", "products": 249, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 95, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-06-28", "text": "This game could have been a lot better, like the first one.  This game has you on so tight of rails it isn't funny.  I suggest the you wait for this one to go on sale during the christmas game sales.", "hours": 13.6, "username": "TurboGuy16", "products": 492, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 95, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-27", "text": "-PC controls are a bit jacked up which is why I went out and bought a wired 360 controller. The game is much easier now. Wont seem to work with any other pc controller\n-The game lacks character customization which i came to believe was standard with most games these days.\n-I would like to see top down view as a choice for camera angle.\n-Great stoyline keeps me interested in whats going to happen.\n-Choices made within the game effect the outcome of the story making it that much more unique.. to an extent, this is not the first game to allow choices in game.\n-Sidequests are available however i would like to see a few more.\n-Graphics even on the lowest setting look fantastic, runs smooth on laptops i5 (until it gets hot and needs to cool for a bit)\n-8/10", "hours": 30.5, "username": "iSkore", "products": 19, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 95, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-26", "text": "Most bugs have been patched - not like the previous two but still decent.", "hours": 39.5, "username": "Xerius", "products": 395, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 95, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-06-25", "text": "Nothing like the other Dungeon siege games.... tisk tisk!", "hours": 0.9, "user_id": "76561197960571151", "username": "Evil^Blade@twitch.tv/evil_blade", "products": 392, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 95, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-06-25", "text": "DO NOT  buy this game !!!! its utterly terrible for what you pay", "hours": 1.0, "username": "Keller", "products": 34, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 95, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-06-24", "text": "This game is terrible.  It is nothing like the first two Dungeon Siege games.  I want my money back.  The camera controls are awful, the voices are poorly done, the multiplayer is terrible, there's no key bindings you can adjust so you're s.o.l. if you're a lefthander like me.  Let the console lamebrains have their \"woo woo kewl graficks\".  Screw you, Obsidian.  your games have all been rubbish and you're certainly not breaking with tradition.", "hours": 1.0, "user_id": "76561197993848116", "username": "Stuffy", "products": 53, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 95, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-06-24", "text": "Don't touch this game with a fourty-foot pole if you are looking to get a Dungeon Siege open world experience, it's not here. This game is on the other hand a great little Hotseat RPG in the spirit of Gauntlet. Graphics are Brilliant and the overall gameplay very satisfying in MP not so much in SP. ~1/10~ (as a Dungeon Siege Title) ~7/10~ (as a Gauntlet title)", "hours": 0.7, "username": "DarkLilly [twitch.tv/darklilly]", "products": 1173, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 95, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-24", "text": "Don't listen to gaming magazines or websites. Dungeon Siege 3 is worth the money. With four characters to play through as, there's tons of replay value. It might seem like a Dragon Age/Mass Effect clone, and there are similarities. The story drags a little at first, and there aren't any customizable controls, which can be frustrating, especially for new players. But the second half of the story is where DS3 shines. The ending, depenant on your choices, is superb.", "hours": 54.0, "username": "KumoKumo", "products": 164, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 95, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-23", "text": "Not as good as the previous Dungeon Siege games, but still a nice game. A little warning if you plan on getting this: make sure to connect a gamepad, the controls for PC suck a bit :)", "hours": 43.9, "username": "Vanitas", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 95, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-06-22", "text": "Do you know what would be a good multiplayer feature? The inability to save.", "hours": 10.1, "username": "mesmermized", "products": 2054, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 96, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-22", "text": "First, a warning: This game is NOTHING like DS1 or 2. Nothing at all. If you were expecting a party-based Diablolike, you won't find it. Obsidian took DS3 in a totally different direction. The random loot/mobs has been watered down, the control over your party's development has been watered down, your ability to control your party itself has been limited, and your progression and potential has been reworked into linear specialization of your basic skills.\nWhen you get over the shock of realizing you're playing a game that's NOT really a DS title, you realize the game stands well on its own. It has a certain charm in the combat, the characters are credible and engaging, and the story is interesting. DS3 should be approached more like The Last Remnant and less like Diablo. Play it for the story and you won't be disappointed... even if the lack of character customization and the limited progression choices hamper replay value.\nWorth checking out the demo before hitting the Buy button.", "hours": 15.2, "username": "Trysdyn", "products": 362, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 96, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-21", "text": "Taken on it's own merits the story is interesting, the playable characters are fun, and the combat handles well while keeping the fights difficult.\nBut do NOT expect Dungeon Siege 3 to be like 1 and 2. I am highly annoyed that this is a console port, and would be a great game if not for my expectation of what a Dungeon Siege title should be.\nThe multiplayer is more like Fable 2 than your typical dungeon crawler. You could even compare it to Hunter: The Reckoning or Marvel Ultimate Alliance. The biggest weakness here is really that the camera locks your team into a small area of movement on screen while enemies will spawn and attack outside of it. You need to move together, while still blocking and dodging, in order to engage targets.\nIt's no wonder why you only get the single player versions of DS1 and 2 when you buy this, LAN either of those 2 games and you will have a vastly improved multiplayer experience...", "hours": 10.5, "username": "Fogg", "products": 459, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 96, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-06-21", "text": "DO NOT BUY THIS GAME. It's horrible. Dungeon siege 2 was better then this crap. Diablo 3 is gonna put this game in it's place. And by place i mean the game is so bad that me taking a crap is better then this.", "hours": 0.2, "username": "\u26c4\ud83c\udf84\ud83c\udf85\ud83c\udffbSanta Gabe\ud83c\udf85\ud83c\udffb\ud83c\udf84\u26c4", "products": 151, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39160", "page": 96, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-06-21", "text": "When I expressed my disappointment in this game, the Dungeon Siege III Developers had this to say:\n\"OH HEY PC GAMERS, WE HEARD YOU LIKED IT WHEN WE TOOK TRADITIONAL PC GAMES, TOLD YOU TO STICK THEM UP YOUR\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 AND THEN PRODUCED A CONSOLE 'TARD-FEST!\nSO WE DID THAT. OKAY?\"\nNo. It's not okay.", "hours": 21.2, "username": "Tizen", "products": 1006, "early_access": false}
